title: round steak with sour cream
directions: Saute meat in butter. Add onion, drained mushrooms, catsup, sour cream, salt and pepper. Simmer 25 minutes. Serve with rice.

title: garden salad
directions: Mix together
cabbage,
onion, sweet pepper and olives. In saucepan mix
vinegar,
mustard,
sugar,
salt, oil, celery seed and black pepper
and bring to a boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture and let cool for awhile.

title: jellied salad
directions: Mix together pretzels, 1/2 cup sugar and butter or oleo.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes.
Let stand until cool.

title: country style chicken
directions: In a large skillet, brown the chicken in butter and olive oil. Place onion around chicken.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover and cook slowly for about 15 minutes.
While chicken is cooking, wash and cut zucchini in 1/2-inch thick slices.
Wash peppers. Remove stems and seeds.
Rinse in cold water and slice lengthwise in 1-inch wide strips.

title: praline candy
directions: Cook water, sugar and vinegar until it forms a hard ball in a cup of cold water (about 20 minutes).
Remove from heat; add butter and nuts.
Beat until it begins to harden.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: egg biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Sift flour, baking powder, sugar and salt. Cut in butter until coarse crumbs.
Stir in milk and egg.
Place on floured surface.
Knead 2 times and roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with 2-inch cutter.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: sour-cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, sour cream, flour and butter.
Add lemon extract and stir.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes; turn oven off and leave pie in oven for 15 minutes more.

title: aimey's specialty
directions: In a large pan, brown beef.
Drain.
Cut potatoes into cubes and add to meat.
Add seasoning.
Cover and let steam until potatoes are tender.
Stir occasionally.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon together.
Cut each biscuit into fourths.
Put sugar mixture in large bowl with cover; toss several biscuits at once.
Place in well-buttered tube or Bundt pan; layer.
Pour melted butter over top and sprinkle remaining cinnamon/sugar mix over top.
Bake at 350° for30 to 35 minutes. Invert onto plate.
Pull apart to eat.
Can add nuts or raisins. Let set 5 minutes to cool.

title: green bean chicken casserole
directions: Cook long grain and wild rice according to directions on box. Add all other ingredients, except paprika and grated Parmesan cheese; mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased 9 x 14-inch glass baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 30 or 40 minutes.
Serves 12 and freezes well.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Peel and put through a sieve or mash well.
Add unbeaten eggs and milk, beat well.
Add melted butter.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 30 minutes in a moderate oven (350°).
Serve hot or cold with whipped cream.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix and put in 2 small crusts or one large crust.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate icebox dessert
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks (beaten), then chocolate, egg whites (beaten), vanilla and walnuts.
Put part of wafers in bottom of pan, then chocolate mixture, then rest of wafers.
Press down in mixture.
Put in refrigerator for 1 hour or so.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients in a deep saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Cook.
Stir
constantly until it forms a soft ball when dropped into
a
glass of cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla flavor and beat until creamy, then add nuts.

title: graham cracker brownies
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Pour into mixing bowl.
Add cream, chocolate and butterscotch morsels and walnuts (if desired).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: kiwi fruit danish
directions: Unroll crescent roll dough and shape into 8 triangles with equal sides.
Combine cream cheese, egg yolk, sugar and almond extract; blend well.
Place 1 tablespoon cream cheese mixture in center of each triangle.
Top with kiwi fruit slice.
Pull points of triangle to center and pinch to seal.
Bake on greased baking sheet at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cook on rack.
Heat jam.
Top each Danish with another kiwi fruit slice; brush with jam.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: my favorite banana bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake in greased loaf pan for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Soften shortening over low heat.
Remove from heat and add sugar, molasses and eggs.
Mix well with a wooden spoon (not mixer).
Sift together dry ingredients and add to first mixture. Mix well with hands.
Chill.

title: pepperoni bread(great for parties!)
directions: I usually make all four loaves in package.
These freeze well, then slice and heat in microwave.

title: pretzel torte
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Reserve 1 cup for top.
Pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan (no bake).
Beat cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip until smooth and spread on crust.
Cook Danish dessert and water until thick.
When cool, mix in raspberries. Put Cool Whip on top and reserved crumbs over.

title: crab meltaways(this is one of my favorites!)
directions: Beat all ingredients well except muffins.
Cut muffins in halves, then into quarters.
Spread crab mixture on top of muffins.
Freeze for at least 30 minutes.
Broil until puffy and golden brown.
Can be frozen several weeks.

title: mrs. freeman's casserole
directions: Brown sausage, pepper and onion.
Drain.
In separate kettle, bring water to boil; add rice and cook uncovered 10 minutes.
Add soup mix and cheese.
Add sausage to rice.
Put all into casserole dish and cook in oven at 350° until bubbly.

title: zucchini-carrot bread #2
directions: Fold
in
dry ingredients thoroughly.
Grease and flour or line with
greased waxed paper 2 loaf pans, 7 1/2 x 3 1/2 x 2-inches or 1 large 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Spoon in batter. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until pick inserted in
center comes our dry.	Wrap well to store.
Bread stays moist for several days.
Bread freezes well.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook the spaghetti until tender. Rinse in cool water and drain well.
Put into
a large serving bowl. Add onion, cucumbers and tomatoes.
Sprinkle with Salad Supreme.
Pour dressing on all. Mix well. Cool a few hours before serving.
Best when served 12 to 24 hours after made. Will keep in refrigerator up to 3 days.

title: lambert's "throwed" rolls
directions: Egg should be at room temperature.
Combine sugar and yeast in tepid water.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes until yeast begins to foam.
Thoroughly mix milk, butter, sugar, egg and salt in large bowl.
Stir in the yeast mixture and 3 1/2 cups of flour, adding a bit more, if necessary, to make a soft pliable dough.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, flour and salt.
Add 1/2 cup milk and 1 egg yolk.
Beat well.
Add other egg yolks and beat thoroughly, then add rest of milk.
Cook until thick.
Be sure to stir constantly. Cool and put in baked pie shell.
Make meringue out of 3 egg whites.
Beat until fluffy, then add 6 tablespoons sugar.

title: glazed vegetables
directions: Cook vegetables in a large pot about 20 minutes; drain well. Place in a 7 x 11-inch baking dish.

title: deluxe sundae
directions: First Layer:
Crush the Oreo cookies.
Mix in 1/2 cup butter. Spread in pan and freeze.

title: cheese balls
directions: Combine cream cheese and Cheddar cheese, mixing well until blended.
Add remaining ingredients, except pecans; mix well. Chill mixture and shape into balls.
Roll into pecans.
Serve with Melba toast or crackers.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix sour cream, soup, chilies and meat in bowl.
If too thick, dilute with drops of milk.

title: sweet & sour meat balls
directions: In a large bowl, combine bread, milk and eggs.
Mix well.
Add meat, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Mix with hand.
Shape into 34 compact golf ball sizes.
Roll in flour and set aside.
In a large skillet, over medium heat, brown meat balls in 1/2 cup of oil until golden brown, remove to a paper towel.
Pour out oil from skillet, return meat balls with cold water, tomato sauce, vinegar, sugar 1 tsp. salt, and sweet gherkin.
Set aside 6 pineapple chunks, then add rest to the meat ball mixture.
Simmer on low heat.
In a medium saucepan, saute in 1 tbsp oil, green peppers, carrots sliced.
Add salt, cook 3-5 minutes.
Then add to meat balls. Spoon into a large serving bowl.
Top with reserved pineapple chunks.
Makes 4-6 Servings over noodles.

title: country potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes before mixing.
Mix first eight ingredients and put in a 9 x 13 inch buttered casserole.
Put 1/4 cup margarine and crushed corn flakes over top.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: crab pate
directions: Heat soup in medium saucepan over low heat.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Add to soup, stirring well.
Add the next 5 ingredients; mix well.
Spoon into oiled 4-cup mold.
Chill until firm overnight.
Unmold and garnish with parsley.
Serve with assorted crackers.
Yields 4 cups.

title: quick cake dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cake mix, pie filling, nuts and eggs.
Mix until blended and creamy.
Pour batter into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Frost with chocolate icing or serve with ice cream.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Place crushed pretzels on a cookie sheet. Bring to a boil the butter and 1/3 cup sugar. Spread over pretzels. Bake at 350° for 5 minutes. Watch closely.
Cool; break up.

title: frijole soup
directions: Cook beans with salt pork until tender.
Drain beans; reserve water.
Puree 1/2 the beans in blender, adding reserved water as needed.
Saute onion and garlic in olive oil.
Add tomatoes and cook 10 minutes.
Add reserved beans and pureed and broth; simmer 20 minutes.
Add reserved water if need soupier.
Place a slice of cheese in bowl.
Pour soup and top with sour cream.

title: frozen fruit delight(just one ingredient!)
directions: Simply put a can of fruit cocktail in your freezer, and leave it there overnight (or until needed).
When you're ready for dessert, just take out the can and run warm water over the outside.
Open both ends of the can.
The frozen fruit slides out easily and can be sliced into 5 sections (each about 3/4-inch thick).
Top with Cool Whip and enjoy!
It's quick, cold, lo-cal, and kids love it!

title: spaghetti
directions: In a large skillet, add hamburger, bell pepper, onion, Italian seasoning, oregano, garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Cook until hamburger is brown.
Drain grease, then add mushrooms and Ragu sauce.
Let simmer for a couple of hours.
Eat spaghetti sauce over spaghetti noodles, or mix them together and place in a pan. Sprinkle with grated cheese and place in oven until cheese has melted.

title: tuna-tomato summer salad
directions: With stem end down, cut each tomato into six wedges, cutting to but not through base of tomato.
Spread wedges apart slightly. Chill.

title: lula yawn's tea cakes
directions: Mix flour, salt, sugar and baking powder.
Add butter to mixture.
Add eggs, vanilla and milk.
Mix well.
Mold tea cakes with hands, about the size of a walnut.
Pat thin.
Bake in lightly greased baking pan for 15 minutes or until golden brown. (Do not overcook.)
This recipe is over 100 years old and does not give oven temperature.
I usually set mine at 400°.

title: dried beef spread
directions: Mix butter and pecans separately to spread on top of the dip. Mix other ingredients together.
Spread in an 8 x 10-inch pie plate. Sprinkle pecan mixture on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Serve hot with crackers.

title: southern green beans
directions: Cook bacon until crispy and set aside. In the hot bacon drippings add the frozen beans, stirring to coat. Cover and cook on medium heat for 5 minutes. Add the onion and season with salt and pepper. Cover and continue to cook until beans are tender and have turned a dark green. Crumble bacon on top and serve.

title: mock steak diane
directions: Cut steak into six serving size pieces.
Combine flour and salt.
Dredge meat in mixture and pound both sides.
Brown meat in cooking fat in large frypan.
Pour off drippings.
Add water. Cover tightly and cook slowly one hour (add more water if necessary).
Combine sherry, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce. Stir into cooking liquid and cook, covered, 25 minutes more or until meat is tender.
Add mushrooms and green onions.
Cook 5 minutes more.
Serves 6.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put oleo in casserole and melt oleo. Put remaining ingredients in buttered casserole.

title: beef and cheese foldovers
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain well.
Place rolls in baking pan with points facing out.
Mix meat and barbecue sauce.
Spread over bottom half of roll; sprinkle with grated cheese.
Fold over points of dough.
Seal seam together.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 375°. Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: grape juice crush
directions: Chill ingredients, then combine, except the ginger ale.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Just before serving, stir in ginger ale.
Serve over crushed ice.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain vegetables well.
Mix thoroughly with remaining ingredients.
Marinate at least overnight.

title: french market soup(serves 10 plus)
directions: Wash and drain 16 bean and peas mix.
Add 3 quarts water with ham hocks and thyme.
Simmer, covered, 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Add next 4 ingredients and salt and pepper.
Simmer, covered, 1 1/2 hours until creamy.
Add sausage and chicken; simmer 30 to 40 more minutes.
Add the optional ingredients, if desired.
Best made the day before!

title: chicken with brown gravy
directions: In Dutch oven, heat oil and brown chicken real well.
Put vegetables in pot and cook until clear.
Put about 1/2 cup flour in and cook until brown.
Put enough water in the pot until desired consistency is reached (about 4 cups).
Put enough Kitchen Bouquet until rich brown color is achieved.
Add bay leaf, thyme and salt and pepper to taste.
Put chicken back in pot and cook until tender, about 1 hour.

title: mom's lemon kool-aid frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth.
Add more water, if needed.

title: cherry marshmallow cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan; line marshmallows evenly in the bottom of the pan and set aside. Prepare cake mix according to package directions with the 1 teaspoon of almond extract. Pour batter over marshmallows. Spoon cherry pie filling evenly over cake batter. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes. The marshmallows will rise to the top of the cake forming a glazed topping. Cool completely before serving.

title: vienna coffee
directions: Using a blender, combine instant coffee, sugar, powdered milk and cinnamon.
For a great cup of coffee, place 2 rounded teaspoonfuls of this mix in a cup of boiling water.
Store unused mix in an airtight container.

title: halibut chowder
directions: In a large kettle combine potatoes, vegetables, onion, celery and water.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and cover.
Let simmer for 20 minutes.
In a saucepan;
melt butter, stir in flour, salt and pepper until smooth.
Gradually add milk.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened.
Add to vegetable mixture. Stir in cooked halibut.

title: pizza bobs
directions: For each person, take 2 slices of bread.
Spread margarine on one side of each slice.
On side without margarine, spread pizza sauce on it; top with pepperoni, then Mozzarella cheese.
Top with other slice of bread with buttered side on the outside.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Turn oven to ??? and bake 10 more minutes.

title: pimento cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients (except nuts) together.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Mold into a ball and roll in chopped nuts.
This can also be used as a spread.
tags: container Cracker Barrel cold pack sharp cheese

title: hot punch
directions: Mix sugar and water and heat.
Add all other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Serve hot.
Good at parties or at Christmas.

title: onion pie
directions: Peel and slice the onions.
In a skillet, heat the butter and saute the sliced onions until clear and tender.
Add salt.
Add the cheese and heat.
Remove the skillet from the heat and allow to cool.
To the onions, add the flour, eggs, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and a few drops of Tabasco.
Stir in the sour cream and heat through.
Set aside and allow to cool slightly. Fill the pie shell with the mixture.
Top with the remaining pastry.
Bake in a 450° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce the heat to 300° and bake until the crust is light brown, about 30 minutes. Cool before serving.
Serves 6.

title: mary-melyssa's favorite banana pudding
directions: Beat instant pudding with milk.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip until mixture is folded together well.
Place layers of wafers and bananas in large bowl.
Pour pudding mixture over wafers and bananas.
Let stand for 2 hours before serving.

title: crock-pot baked beans
directions: Cook beans in salted water along with the minced onion on top of stove until tender.
Add (after draining off the water) all the other ingredients and put in crock-pot to cook the bacon and flavor the beans, 1 hour on high.
If too dry, add some of the drained off water at anytime.
Won't hurt to cook longer in crock-pot on low.

title: prune cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients and sift together.
Stir in oil, eggs, buttermilk and prunes.
Mix well, then add nuts (if desired). Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. While still hot in pan, add Topping.
Cut into squares.

title: venison in a wok
directions: Slice meat to 1/16-inch strips; cut against grain.
Marinate the meat in a bowl with oil, soy sauce, ginger and cayenne pepper mixture.
Refrigerate 3 hours.
Just before cooking, slice and chop vegetables.
Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a wok (375° for electric wok).
Place meat in hot oil and stir-fry for 3 minutes. Push the meat up to the sides and add onions.
Stir-fry 2 minutes. Push up the side and add mushrooms.
Stir-fry 2 minutes. Stir-fry celery for 2 minutes.
Push to side and stir-fry green peppers for 1 minute.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown beef, onion and celery in shortening.
Add bean sprouts and chop suey vegetables.
Cook on low for 1 hour, stirring occasionally, covered.
Mix soy sauce and flour.
Add to pot slowly.
When thickened, add molasses.
Simmer 15 minutes, uncovered.
Serve with rice, noodles or potatoes.
Great with chow mein noodles on top.

title: heaven's lemonade cake
directions: Put evaporated milk in freezer and shake every 15 minutes to keep from freezing on side of can until chilled.
In small saucepan, mix gelatin and sugar.
Add egg substitute and water. Cook and stir until gelatin dissolves and mixture thickens just slightly; remove from heat.
Stir in concentrate.
Chill until partially set.
Tear cake into bite-size pieces.
Set aside.
Pour cold evaporated milk in large bowl and whip until it holds peaks. Tint yellow.
Fold lemonade mixture into whipped milk.
Cover bottom of 10-inch tube pan with thin layer of lemonade mixture. Arrange 1/3 of cake on top.
Pour 1/3 of remaining lemonade mixture over.
Repeat layers.
Chill until firm.
Unmold on serving plate. Makes 16 servings.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows together.
Pour mixture over popcorn.
Rub some butter on hands and quickly shape into balls.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into small pieces (takes about 2 months).
Add enough gravy to cover.
Cook over kerosene fire for 4 weeks at 465°.
Serves 3,800 people.
If more are expected, add the two rabbits.
But do this only if necessary, as most people don't like hare in their stew.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Add broth, onion, eggs, Veg-All and 3 cans of soup.

title: southern sweet potato pecan bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease bottom of an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Stir together flour, baking powder, salt and spices in mixing bowl.
With a spoon, stir in sugar, eggs, oil and milk.
Stir to blend.
Stir in sweet potatoes, pecans and raisins. Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.
For easier slicing, wrap loaf and store overnight in a cool place.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, butter and other ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes; turn down to 350° and bake until firm.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix together the Raisin Bran, sugar, flour, soda and salt. Mix the eggs, Wesson oil and buttermilk together and add to the first mixture.
Store, covered, in refrigerator.
Will keep at least 6 weeks. Use as needed.

title: white trash
directions: Melt chocolate in microwave.
Mix in all other ingredients. Stir well.
Spread on wax paper to cool.
Break into pieces and refrigerate.
Can be frozen.

title: rice meat balls
directions: Combine rice with beef, egg, onion, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup tomato juice. Mix lightly. Shape mixture into 18 balls.
Place in skillet. Add sugar to remaining 2 cups tomato juice. Pour juice over meat balls in skillet. Bring mixture to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer and cover 15 minutes, basting occasionally.

title: sunday chicken
directions: Cook chicken, debone and reserve 2 cups of broth.
Chop meat and set aside.
Melt butter in large skillet, saute celery and onion; add all ingredients.
Spoon mixture into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish and top with stuffing prepared according to the package.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: crunchy oriental pork casserole
directions: Combine soup, milk and soy sauce; add remaining ingredients. Put into shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with rest of can of noodles.
Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes.
Serve with soy sauce if desired.

title: party salad
directions: Mix above ingredients together.
Put in glass dish.
Let stand in refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: ice cream sandwiches
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut frozen cookie dough into 16 slices. Place cookie dough slices on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until golden.
Let stand 1 minute.
Remove cookies to wire racks.
Cool completely.
Spread 1/3 cup ice cream onto 8 cookies. Top with remaining cookies.
Freeze sandwiches until ready to serve.
Makes 8 servings.

title: delightful layered salad
directions: Melt butter.
Mix with flour, nuts and sugar. Pat firmly onto bottom of 8 x 11-inch glass baking dish.
Bake for 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool well.

title: watergate salad
directions: Use pudding as it is straight from the box.
In a large dish, layer ingredients as listed: pineapple, marshmallows, coconut, pudding, Cool Whip and pecans.
Do not stir.
Refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.

title: vichyssoise
directions: Cut the leeks into 1/4-inch slices, using the white parts plus about 1 inch of the lightest green parts.
Chop the onion finely.

title: quick cheese bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan. Beat eggs in large bowl. Stir in water. Add biscuit mix and beat. Add mustard and 1 cup cheese. Mix thoroughly. Turn batter into pan. Sprinkle with remaining cheese and dot with butter. Bake 45 minutes. Cool before slicing.

title: spanish rice
directions: Slice bacon into small pieces and fry.
Before done, add onions and saute.
Add other ingredients and simmer until hot.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Mix by hand (won't be completely smooth).
Let stand 5 minutes. Put icing in bottom of casserole (Tupperware with cone). Pour cake mix in.
Cook in microwave on High power 14 minutes.
If doesn't come away from side, cook another minute or two.
Let stand 20 minutes, then turn out on plate.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flavorings.
Mix flour and milk into creamed mixture alternately, beginning and ending with flour.
Bake at 315° to 325° for 1 1/4 hours in greased tube pan.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Boil chicken. Remove meat from bone and cube. Melt butter in a skillet. Add onion, bell pepper, wine and spices. Saut until tender. Add chicken. Simmer until liquid is absorbed. Place a small amount of mixture in a warm tortilla. Top with cheese and picante sauce. Roll up.

title: cheesy meat casserole
directions: Mix soup with milk.
Combine all ingredients in greased 2-quart casserole. Pour over soup.
Top with cheese and toasted bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix beef, rice and salt and pepper in bowl until well blended.

title: party spareribs
directions: Place spareribs, meat side up, in shallow baking pan.
Sprinkle with salt.
Top with lemon slices.
Bake in 350° oven 30 minutes. Combine remaining ingredients.
Brush ribs with mixture.
Turn and continue baking 1 hour longer, basting frequently.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: beef tenderloin
directions: Get the butcher to cut you any size piece of a beef tenderloin.
Ice the beef tenderloin with softened butter mixed with 2 to 3 teaspoons David Wade's Worcestershire powder.
Wrap tightly in heavy-duty foil.
Bake in the oven at 325° until done. The gravy is delicious.
Slice the meat on a platter.
Pour the gravy over the slices.

title: eggplant
directions: Peel and slice eggplant very very thin (less than 1/4-inch). Dip eggplant in flour, then egg mix (eggs, cheese, parsley and basil).
Lightly oil a cookie sheet.
Place slices on cookie sheet and bake in 350° oven for approximately 10 minutes, turn and bake 10 minutes.
Remove eggplant and layer in casserole with tomato sauce and grated cheese.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Mix well and pour into pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 35-40 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onion and pepper in margarine.
Add flour.
Stir in milk.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into large casserole dish. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: cracker salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well, then refrigerate overnight or longer.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat egg yolks and add to flour, sugar and milk.
Cook on stove until real thick, then add vanilla and cocoa. Pour in pie crust.
Put meringue on top.
Bake at 325° until meringue browns.

title: chess cake
directions: In a saucepan on top of the stove, melt margarine over medium heat.
Next, add both brown and white sugars to margarine and continue to melt, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat and stir in flour.
Add eggs, one at a time, and fold into mixture.
When well mixed, add flavoring and nuts by folding into mixture.
Pour mixture into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for about 50 minutes.
This cake falls to make its wonderful taste.
Sometimes if it rises too much, bang the pan to help it fall.
Dust top with confectioners sugar.
Cool before cutting.

title: dieters' barbecue chicken
directions: Roll cut up chicken into milk and egg mix.
Roll into pork skin crumbs.
Spray baking dish with Pam no stick.
Cover and bake 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes in a 450° oven.

title: party dip
directions: Mix milk, cream cheese and sour cream.
Add onion flakes and sweet pepper flakes; stir well.
Add finely chopped dried beef; mix well.
Chill overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: pineapple topped cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Boil pineapple and sugar 5 minutes.
Punch holes in cake and pour over hot cake. Refrigerate until cool.
Mix pudding, using 1 1/2 cups milk.
Let stand until thick.
Fold Cool Whip into pudding and spread over cooled cake.
Top with coconut.

title: smoked goose or duck breasts
directions: If using oven only, add 2 tsp. liquid smoke to brine.

title: best beef stew
directions: Season beef cubes with tenderizer and seasoned salt.
Brown in oil.
On high heat, add water, onions and celery.
Bring to boil. Add water if necessary.
Reduce heat to simmer for 2 hours.
Add carrots.
Bring to boil and cook for 15 minutes.
Add potatoes, water, paprika, bay leaves, marjoram and thyme.
Cover and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with buttered crusty-type bread and cole slaw.

title: spinach shrimp casserole
directions: In bowl, combine beaten eggs, cooked orzo, 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce and Parmesan cheese. Grease 9-inch pie plate. Spread mixture over bottom and up side of pan to make a "crust." Drain cooked spinach well. In another bowl, combine spinach, Ricotta cheese, nutmeg and shrimp. Spoon into pie plate. Spread remaining spaghetti sauce over filling. Cover edge of plate with a small piece of foil to prevent burning. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove from oven and bake an additional 3 to 5 minutes or until cheese is melted. Makes 8 large servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain vegetables well.
In a buttered baking dish, put a layer of asparagus, a layer of carrots and a layer of peas.
Cover with grated cheese.
Add a can of undiluted mushroom soup.
Cover with a can of French fried onions.
Cover and bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Makes a great no-meat main dish.

title: special potatoes
directions: Combine and heat all ingredients, except hash browns and cornflakes.
Place hash browns in a 2-quart casserole dish; pour warm mixture over hash browns.
Sprinkle cornflakes on top.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Serves 6.

title: refrigerator yeast dough
directions: Stir yeast into warm water.
Grease Tupperware container.
Mix together eggs, sugar, yeast mixture and melted shortening (lukewarm).
Add flour and salt.
Stir.
Put mixture in refrigerator overnight or 3 hours.

title: pecan lassies
directions: Cream together the cheese, butter and flour; chill for several hours.
When pastry has chilled, form into small balls.
Press a ball into each miniature muffin tin cup, bringing dough up around sides.

title: no sugar cake
directions: Cook raisins in 2 cups water until plump.
Drain and cool. Mix all ingredients, using a spoon.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. (Recipe can be halved.
Cook for about 40 minutes.)

title: blueberry squares(raspberry or blackberry)
directions: Mix all dry ingredients as for pie dough.
Beat egg yolks, milk and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients.
Chill 1 hour.

title: blueberry streusel cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut margarine into dry cake mix until crumbly.
Stir in pecans and cinnamon.
Reserve 1 cup of the crumbly mixture.
Press remaining crumbly mixture on bottom and about halfway up sides of ungreased 9 x 3-inch spring-form pan.
tags: Betty Crocker golden pound cake mix

title: mama's tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Alternate dry ingredients with milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Take about half of the dough and place on a floured board or clean countertop.
Mix some more flour until it is not too sticky.
Roll out thick and cut.
Bake at 350° on greased cookie sheet until done.
Repeat for the other half of the dough.
Recipe makes about 4 1/2 dozen tea cakes.

title: pear cake with caramel drizzle
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add vanilla.
Combine flours and next 3 ingredients; add to sugar mixture alternately with pears.
Stir in pecans.
Spoon into a well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 375° for 55 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and let cool completely on wire rack.
Spoon Caramel Drizzle over cake.

title: toastee oatmeal cookies
directions: Brown margarine.
Add oatmeal.
Stir constantly for 5 minutes or until lightly brown.
Remove from heat.
In a large mixing bowl, cream together brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture.
Stir until creamy.
Add toasted oatmeal.

title: geri's oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl blend both sugars, flour and uncooked oatmeal.
Add eggs and water to mixture and blend together well.
Drop cookies by teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet about 1 inch apart.
Cook about 8 minutes or until golden brown.

title: scalloped potatoes with ham
directions: Saute onions in butter.

title: strawberry crunch
directions: In 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, mix flour, brown sugar, nuts and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; stir often.

title: vegetable-beef stir-fry
directions: Mix beef, water, soy sauce and cornstarch in small bowl.
Heat vegetable oil in large skillet.
Add garlic.
Cook 15 to 30 seconds.
Add carrots, broccoli and beef broth.
Cover.
Reduce heat; simmer 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir beef-cornstarch mixture.
Mix in skillet.
Reheat to medium-high.
Stir 1 to 2 minutes, until meat is no longer red and sauce is boiling.
Stir in sesame oil.

title: party potatoes
directions: Add cream cheese, sour cream and garlic salt to mashed potatoes.
Mix until fluffy.
Pour into a casserole.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: pork chops
directions: Slice
potatoes
thin and spread over bottom of greased pan. Slice
onion and spread over potatoes.
Brown pork chops in skillet.
Salt
and
pepper
to taste.
Lay on top of potatoes. In
bowl,
mix
soup
and milk.
Pour over potatoes and pork chops.
Put in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: caramel skillet cake
directions: Boil the brown sugar, water and 2 tablespoons butter 3 minutes in skillet. Combine the sugar, 2 tablespoons butter, baking powder, milk and flour. Drop by teaspoon in caramel sauce. Cook on medium heat for 20 minutes with lid on.

title: "praise the lord muffins"
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon and ginger. Stir in carrots and raisins.
Separately combine undrained pineapple, eggs, butter and vanilla.
Stir into dry ingredients until just blended.
Spoon into 12 greased muffin tins.
Bake at 375° for about 25 to 27 minutes.
Turn on rack to cool.
Serves 12.

title: wendy's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, brown sugar and sugar.
Beat in egg, vanilla and cold water; then add flour, baking soda and salt. Mix well.
Stir in oatmeal, raisins and nuts.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto a cookie sheet lightly greased with shortening.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
(Use top oven rack.)

title: homemade baked beans
directions: Cook beans in salted water until done.
Mix all ingredients and add to cooked beans.
Bake for 3 hours in very slow oven at 275°.
Can be stored.

title: ham and broccoli casserole
directions: In a saucepan, heat to simmer the soups, milk, water and butter, stirring frequently.
In a buttered casserole dish, mix soup with the rest of the ingredients. Cover and bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender. Blend until smooth.
Makes 3 cups.

title: macaroni and tuna salad
directions: Boil macaroni in salt water until tender.
Drain and rinse with cold water; drain.
Mix with tuna, eggs, green pepper, celery and mayonnaise.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine peanut butter, Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of mixer until well blended. Add egg and beat until blended.
Combine flour, salt and soda. Add creamed mixture at low speed.
Mix just until blended.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls, 2-inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Cool 2 minutes before removing from cookie sheet.

title: apple crunch pie
directions: Place rack in lowest position in oven, preheated to 425°. Spoon apple filling into pastry shell.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: salad oil pie crust
directions: Mix all together and roll between wax paper.
Excellent even if you re-roll it!
Makes 1 double pie crust.

title: corn souffle
directions: Mix all together well.
Pour in lightly greased baking dish or casserole.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Blend condensed milk, Cool Whip and pineapple together.
Add pecans to this mixture.
Add lemon juice to the mixture.
The lemon juice will stiffen your filling.
Place mixture in a graham cracker crust.
Chill and serve cold.

title: chili seasoning
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in small airtight jar in a cool dry place.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: philadelphia cream cheese pound cake
directions: Combine butter and margarine and cream cheese.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add salt and vanilla.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Add flour 1 cup at a time.
Beat well. Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan. Place in cold oven. Turn on oven at 275° for 1 hour; turn up to 300° and bake for 30 minutes more.
Test for doneness with a toothpick.
Cool cake in pan 25 minutes before trying to remove it.

title: sauteed mushrooms
directions: Rinse; pat dry mushrooms.
Slice or drain canned.
Set aside. Saute onions in butter in large skillet 2 minutes.
Add mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Saute for 3 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: hamburger italiano
directions: Cook noodles 3 minutes as package directs with 1 soup base. Drain and rinse in hot water. Place on serving platter; keep warm. Saute ground beef with onions; drain. Stir in tomato sauce, herbs and remaining soup base. Cook 5 minutes. Spoon sauce over noodles. Sprinkle with parmesan cheese. Toss just before serving.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook jumbo shells first; rinse with cool water and drain well. Set to dry.
Mix all ingredients together (except spaghetti sauce and Mozzarella cheese).
Stuff shells with mixture.
Put in large cake pan (9 x 13-inch), then cover with spaghetti sauce.
Spread with Mozzarella cheese.
Cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cherry squares
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add beaten eggs; mix well.
Add flour, almond extract and vanilla extract.
Place in greased jelly roll pan.
Top with pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: oven style swiss steak
directions: Trim fat from meat.
Pound meat with meat mallet.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place meat in 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.
Top with onions and mushrooms.
Pour sauce over all. Cook, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover, cook 15 minutes longer.
Baste occasionally.
To serve, spoon sauce over meat. Serves 8.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Add flour, sugar and brown sugar; beat until well blended.
Blend in melted butter.
Stir in chocolate morsels and walnuts.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chicken pasta casserole or salad
directions: Cook shells according to package instructions. (Do not overcook!)
Drain and put in a bowl or baking dish.
Microwave chicken breasts on High, on both sides, until done (6 to 8 minutes each side).
Let cool some and dice into bite sizes.
Cook peas in boiling water just until heated, then drain.
Add shells, olives, peas, onion and celery and mix with mayonnaise.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onions; drain most of the grease.
Add all of the ingredients except spices.
Combine spices in a large dry jar.
Shake well and then add to mixture slowly.
Cook 1/2 hour and serve.

title: donn's hot chili
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pot.
Cook covered for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover and cook for another 30 minutes.
During the last 5 minutes of cooking, add 1 teaspoon cayenne pepper.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crackers and butter.
Melt butter; mix well with crackers.
Sprinkle cracker mixture on top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: mexicali bean pot
directions: Put pork and beans in a 2-quart casserole.
Very gently, stir in tomato, onion, cheese and peppers.
Cover and bake 45
minutes at 350°.
Remove lid and bake, uncovered, for 15 more minutes.

title: barbecue baked potatoes and skins
directions: Scrub the potatoes; wipe dry.
Rub generously with butter; add salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Wrap potatoes twice in aluminum foil.
Place on the grill for approximately 50 minutes or until they are soft.
After about 35 minutes, move away from the hot coals.
Serves six.

title: veal paprikash
directions: Cut veal into bite size pieces.
Brown the veal in fat slowly, turning meat as it browns.
Add sliced onion and cook until they are lightly browned.
Add water in which you have dissolved the bouillon cubes, salt and paprika.
Cover and cook over a low flame for about one hour or until meat is tender.
Add more water as needed.
When meat is done, blend flour with about 2 tablespoons of water into a smooth paste.
Stir into the meat mixture and let cook until thickened.
Just before serving, add the sour cream. Heat, but do not boil, because the cream will curdle.
Serve with noodles or spatzle.
Serves two.

title: unbelievable brownies
directions: Melt butter with chocolate.
In a separate bowl, combine eggs and sugar.
Mix well.
Add vanilla.
Add flour and mix well.
Beat in chocolate mixture.
Add chocolate chips (be generous and creative with amount and types of chips).
Stir into batter well. Pour batter into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peppermint punch
directions: Spoon ice cream into punch bowl.
Add eggnog and chilled club soda and mix well.	Stir in food coloring.	Spoon whipped cream over surface and mix gently.
To serve fill punch cup; put a spoonful more whipped cream and sprinkle with crushed peppermint and add a peppermint stick.
Makes sixteen 4-ounce servings.

title: acini de pepe salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni and set aside.
Drain fruit and save juice.
Mix together in saucepan the sugar, flour, beaten eggs and reserved juices.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly; cool.

title: grape-nut pudding
directions: In your electric mixing bowl, put 1 to 5 ingredients.
Beat at low speed for 2 to 3 minutes.
Put in greased deep dish; bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Chill and serve with whipped cream.

title: italian bean soup
directions: Sort and wash beans.
Place in Dutch oven.
Cover with water 2-inches above beans.
Bring to a boil.
Cook over high heat 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 1 hour.
Drain beans.
Add 2 quarts of water and next 10 ingredients.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender, stirring occasionally.
Add macaroni and cook uncovered 10 minutes or until macaroni is tender.
Yields 14 servings.
Preparation Time:
3 1/2 hours.

title: pull apart
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 8x4-inch loaf pan.
In a small bowl, add sugar and cinnamon; blend well and set aside.
Melt butter in a separate bowl.
Cut biscuits into quarters.
Dip each quarter into melted butter, roll in cinnamon sugar mixture, and drop in loaf pan.
Bake at 400° for 20-27 minutes.
Cool a few minutes and loosen edges.
Tip over onto plate, top with Cool Whip, and serve warm!

title: cranberry freeze
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Can either be served as is after being chilled or pour into cupcake papers and freeze.
To serve, garnish plate with lettuce leaf.
Thaw individual cups and turn out on lettuce leaf.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat ingredients together.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Can be served with cream cheese or cream cheese and powdered sugar mixed.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, stir together sugar and syrup. Cook 4 minutes on High setting in microwave.
Stir in peanuts. Then cook 4 more minutes on High.
Stir well and add vanilla and butter.
Cook 1 minute longer on High.
Stir.
Add soda and quickly stir until light and foamy.
Immediately pour onto a lightly buttered baking sheet.
Spread out thin.
When cool, break into pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: eggplant  casserole
directions: Place a layer of sliced eggplant on the bottom of a baking dish.
Top with a layer of sliced tomatoes.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Dot with butter; salt and pepper to taste.
Repeat with 3 or 4 layers of each.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: christmas cake
directions: Mix together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Drop on cookie sheet with teaspoon. Flatten a little. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: after dinner mint shakes
directions: Place 1 cup of ice cream in a Tupperware Quick Shake container. Add 1/4 cup milk, 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and a few drops of mint flavoring.
Apply seal and cap, shake until well combined.
Pour into a 12 ounce tumbler.
Repeat, using the same amounts of ice cream, milk, vanilla and mint flavoring, to fill tumbler.
With remaining ice cream, milk, vanilla and mint flavoring, prepare a second shake, following the same two-step procedure used to make first shake.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Let cool until firm.

title: crock-pot roast
directions: Wash roast; season with tenderizer, salt and pepper to taste. Place 1/2 of ingredients in bottom of crock-pot.
Place roast in pot.
Put remaining ingredients over roast.
Cook on High for 4 hours or on low for 6 hours.

title: no mayonnaise potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water 20 minutes or until tender. When cool enough to handle, but still warm, peel and cut into 1-inch cubes.

title: graham cracker brownies
directions: Crush graham crackers into crumbs.
Mix all ingredients together and place in 8 x 14-inch greased pan.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut.
Top with sifted confectioners sugar.

title: roasted pecans
directions: Place pecans in shallow roasting pan.
Melt butter and drizzle over pecans and lightly salt.
Bake at 200° for 2 hours, stirring every 10 minutes.

title: thanksgiving cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve
Jell-O
in
boiling water.
Mix pineapple and sugar together and add to Jell-O.
Put into refrigerator until slightly jelled.
Add oranges, cranberries and nuts.
Put into a mold for a beautiful congealed salad.

title: butterscotch fingers
directions: Preheat your oven to 325°.
Use a small piece of waxed paper or your clean fingertips to grease the pan by lightly spreading shortening over the bottom and sides.
Sift flour once, then measure.
Remember the instructions in introduction to measuring. Measure the brown sugar.
Measure baking powder; add to the flour and sift again.
Break one egg in at a time into a small bowl.
To do this, hold the egg in one hand.
Hold a knife in your other hand and hit the egg hard enough with the shell lightly.
Then hold the egg with both hands over the dish.
Put both thumbs together in the break and pull apart.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Brown beef and drain fat. Add sauce, water, salt and sugar. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes. In 13 3/4 x 8 1/2-inch casserole, layer 1/3 of sauce, 1/2 of uncooked noodles, 1 cup cottage cheese, 1/4 cup Parmesan and 1 cup Mozzarella cheese. Repeat, ending with Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses. Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes. Remove foil and let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: easy avocado dip
directions: Mash avocado with fork until smooth.
Add other ingredients and stir well.
Serve with potato, corn or tortilla chips.

title: hopping john(an old southern dish)
directions: *(I prefer salt pork.)

title: country pie
directions: Mix ground beef, 4 ounces tomato sauce, salt and pepper (sage, if desired).
Spread on bottom and sides of casserole dish.
Mix cooked rice, salt and tomato sauce (use as filling).
Top with sliced Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown around edges.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Brown diced onion in liquid Butter Buds.
Add cooked ground turkey.
Stir refried beans into turkey mixture.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish that has been sprayed with nonfat cooking spray.
Sprinkle green chiles over top of turkey-bean mixture. Spread half of cheese over this.
Pour taco sauce over cheese. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool slightly and spoon mock sour cream to make a cross on top of casserole.
Serve with Guiltless Gourmet low-fat tortilla chips or homemade low-fat chips.
Yields 12 servings.

title: beef nut casserole
directions: Brown meat; cook noodles.
Mix browned meat, noodles, soup and water.
Put in oven baking dish and bake for 30 to 35 minutes, then put chow mein noodles on top of casserole.
Sprinkle nuts over chow mein noodles and return to oven for 10 or 15 minutes or until nuts are browned.

title: banana punch
directions: Boil together first 2 ingredients.
Add remaining.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar. Add eggs. Beat well. Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture. Add pecans. Spoon onto a greased cookie sheet. One tablespoon of mixture makes a good size cookie. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes approximately 5 dozen.

title: corn flakes candy
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and cream to
soft
ball test in cold water. Remove from fire, add
butter
and vanilla.
Pour over cereals and nuts, combined.
In
a
big
bowl, mix thoroughly; press into buttered pan.
Cut in squares when cold.

title: peanut butter tandy cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in 2 jelly roll pans at 350° about 15	to
20	minutes.
Keep	checking.
Remove from oven. Spread with 12 ounces peanut butter on hot cakes.	Refrigerate until cool.
Melt two 8 ounce Hershey bars or use Nestle candy coating chocolate.	Spread	on
cool
cakes.
Refrigerate
1/2 hour.

title: spiced orange tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and store airtight.
To make 1 cup spiced orange tea, place 1 tablespoon of mix in a cup.
Pour in 1 cup boiling water and stir until dissolved.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Clean and slice carrots; blanch about 10 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Layer in a bowl with onion and bell pepper.
Combine all remaining ingredients and pour over carrot mixture.
Marinate 24 hours in a covered dish in refrigerator.
Will keep one week.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix milk, margarine, sugar and eggs. Add dry ingredients.
Fold in nuts and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cook in unbaked pie shell.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Soften butter or margarine in mixing bowl.
Add cheese, salt and cayenne and mix until well blended.
Add flour and mix well. Shape dough into rolls, about 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill overnight in refrigerator.

title: ross' dip
directions: Put all ingredients into a food processor.
Mix well until creamy and smooth.
Chill.
Serve with raw vegetables or chips.

title: beef shau mai
directions: Filling:
Mix ground beef and rest of the ingredients thoroughly until the meat is sticky, then marinate it for 10 minutes. Squeeze 1 portion of the filling into a ball.
Dip a spoon in water, then use the spoon to remove the meatball. Place the meatball on a leaf. Arrange the meatballs in a steamer and steam over high heat for 8 minutes.

title: pumpkin goodie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into ungreased 8 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle one box plain yellow cake mix on top.
Sprinkle 1 cup walnuts over that and pour 1/4 cup melted oleo over top.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Wash chicken under hot water.
Pat dry.
Cut into 1/2-inch cubes. Mix the egg whites, salt and cornstarch.
Add chicken and toss to coat.
Refrigerate covered for at least 20 to 30 minutes. (Dish can be done in advance to this point.)

title: creamy banana fudge shake
directions: Process
bananas,
cocoa,
sweetener, yogurt and ice in blender
until smooth.
Pour into glasses and serve immediately. Makes 2 servings.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Fix the muffin mix according to the directions on package and bake.
When done, crumble it up.
Cut tomato, onion and green pepper and add mayonnaise to taste.
Toss with bread crumbs.

title: western flapjacks
directions: Mix all dry ingredients; add oil, egg yolks and buttermilk. Beat egg whites and fold into mixture.

title: lazy boy cobbler
directions: * Amount of fruit:
Use 1 freezer pint bag or large can if using peaches.

title: easy bran muffin mix
directions: In a large bowl, sift together flour, sugar, soda and salt. Add nut meats, if desired.
Beat eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Add dry ingredients, nuts and cereal and mix well.
Store in closed container.
Refrigerate when ready to bake.
Put in paper lined muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
This mix will keep in refrigerator for 2 to 3 weeks, so it may be baked a small portion at a time.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cream butter and sugar together until fluffy. Add eggs and beat well. Sift together flour, salt and baking powder. Add to butter mixture. Add sour cream, bananas and vanilla. Stir by hand. Add chocolate chips. Pour into greased and floured large loaf pan. Bake 1 hour or until knife comes out clean. Let cool and slice.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Thaw and drain strawberries.
Have your pie crusts ready.
Mix milk, Cool Whip, strawberries and pecans well.
Add lemon juice and mix until thick.
Pour into pie shells and refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: scalloped eggplant
directions: Slice, peel and medium dice eggplant.
In a medium size saucepan, add chunks of eggplant, salt and water.
Boil until tender.
Cool and then drain.
Mix egg and milk mixture with eggplant chunks; add margarine spoonfuls and crackers.
If too juicy, add more crumbled crackers.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with additional cracker crumbs and dabs of butter or margarine.
Sprinkle parsley flakes and paprika on top. Bake at 350° until golden brown on top and mix has set.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Enjoy!

title: cherry cheesecake pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Gradually add milk and stir until blended.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla. Turn into crust.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Garnish with chilled cherry pie filling just before serving.

title: good veggie dip
directions: Mix well and serve with any raw vegetables.

title: brownies-hepburn
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt chocolate and butter over very low heat in heavy saucepan.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Quickly stir in walnuts, flour and salt. Spread batter in well-greased 8 x 8-inch baking pan and bake for 40 to 45 minutes.
Remove pan to a rack to cool.
Cut into 12 pieces.

title: cottage fries
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle dried onion rings on top of the potatoes and cover.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour for a flat pan.

title: holiday conserve(makes six 8-ounce jars)
directions: Add just enough water to cover apricots; bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes. Drain and chop. Reserve 1/2 cup of the juice. Combine apricots, juice, drained pineapple, raisins, nuts and lemon juice in a 4-quart pan. Add sugar; stir to blend well. Bring mixture to a full boil over high heat, stirring constantly. When conserve is bubbling rapidly over surface, boil hard 1 minute longer. Remove from heat. Stir in pectin. Ladle conserve in jars taken from hot water. Seal with lids or paraffin.

title: holly candy
directions: With your stove on low flame, mix the butter and marshmallows together until melted.
Next add vanilla and food coloring.
Mix that in and then add the cornflakes and stir until they are well coated.
Drop by teaspoons on wax paper and then you may add red hots on them, if so desired.

title: sticky buns
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Put ingredients into greased pan.
Add biscuits on top.
Bake for 10 minutes. Turn upside down on plate for 2 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar, then add water and syrup.
Cook until thick and clear.
While hot, add Jell-O, food coloring and vanilla; cool.
Wash strawberries and slice.
Add to cooled ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: chinese fish and vegetables
directions: Wipe fish pieces dry.
Dredge lightly in cornstarch.
Heat oil in skillet and brown fish quickly on both sides. While fish browns, prepare vegetables.
Mince finely the garlic, ginger root and onion. Combine in bowl the remaining ingredients.

Remove fish from skillet. Add 1 tablespoon oil and heat. Add minced vegetables and then sliced vegetables. Stir-fry 1 minute. Add liquid and bring to a boil. Return fish to skillet. Simmer, covered, about 5 minutes until fish is done and vegetables are crisp-tender.
Serve over hot rice. Serves 6.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Spray large skillet with Pam.
Melt four tablespoons of butter in skillet.
Saute pepper and onions with a sprinkle of Equal (sugar) until about half transparent.
Add chicken breast on one side of skillet. Brown both sides.
Stir pepper and onions around on top and add chunked pineapple.
Simmer for about 30 minutes on low.

title: chicken scampi
directions: In frypan with butter or oleo, saute mushrooms.
Remove with slotted spoon and put in bottom of casserole.
Saute chicken and garlic until chicken turns white.

title: pecan-crumble sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In medium bowl, combine flour, sugar and allspice; mix well.
With pastry blender or two knives, cut in butter until mixture forms coarse crumbs; set aside.

title: goofballs
directions: Melt caramels and Eagle Brand together in double boiler.
Dip marshmallows into caramel mixture (use toothpicks).
Drop into bowl of Rice Krispies.
Shake bowl so Rice Krispies cover marshmallows completely.

title: ruth's zucchini bread
directions: Put flour, zucchini, sugar, coconut and nuts in a large bowl and mix.
Add baking soda, baking powder and salt, and then add vanilla, oil and eggs.
Mix all together very well.
Put in two greased 5 1/2 x 9 1/2-inch loaf pans, filling each about half full.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pumpkin cake bars
directions: Beat sugar, oil, pumpkin and eggs in a large mixing bowl on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally, 1 minute.
Stir in Bisquick, cinnamon and raisins. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan (or 2 jelly roll pans).
Bake until wooden pick comes out clean, 25 to 30 minutes. Cool. Frost.

title: chocolate bars
directions: Beat margarine and 1 egg.
Stir in flour, 3 teaspoons of sugar and 1 teaspoon of baking powder.
Mix well.
Press evenly in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: southern gal biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Blend in shortening until it looks like corn meal.
Pour in milk slowly.
Mix with fork.
Add eggs.
Stir to a stiff dough.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sausage dip
directions: Cook sausage until browned; drain excess fat.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Cut Velveeta and spread over sausage and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Bake at 425° until bubbling.

title: cherry nut cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt; add gradually with milk and vanilla.
Lastly add nuts and cherries.
Will make stiff dough.
Bake in slow oven for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheesy sausage dip
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler.
Add rest of ingredients, mixing well.
Serve hot with tostados.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Sprinkle nuts and coconut on bottom of 9 x 13 greased pan. Prepare cake mix according to directions and pour over nuts and coconut.
Melt butter; add cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Spread over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cranberry relish
directions: *You can use all cherry jello, but the lemon is pretty.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix butter, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, sour cream and zucchini.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes until done in center.

title: taco surprise
directions: For large party, double recipe.

title: cocktail rye appetizers
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Spread on party rye bread and top with thin slice of cucumber.

title: sicilian style hot turkey sausage
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly with hands to distribute spices evenly.
Shape mixture into 8 patties. Refrigerate, covered, up to several hours.
To cook patties, lightly oil bottom of skillet.
Add just enough water to cover bottom.
Add patties to skillet, making sure they do not touch. Cook uncovered over medium heat, turning once, until browned and cooked through, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Beat cream cheese until fairly smooth.
Add Cool Whip.
Blend. Add dry jello mix.
Mix well, then add pineapple and pecans. Chill for several hours.

title: beef and rice casserole
directions: Lightly brown beef, onion and pepper in fat.
Wash rice. Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Cut slices of fresh bread into rounds using a biscuit cutter. Melt oleo and brush inside of small muffin tins.
Fit bread rounds into cups, handling carefully to avoid tearing.
Brush inside of bread cups with oleo.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes or just until lightly browned.
Remove from tins immediately.
These little cups are excellent for using with any creamed dish or meat mixture with sauce.

title: red hot chili
directions: Brown beef until crumbles.
Add garlic at same time.
When brown, add the rest of ingredients and mix well.
Bring to low boil and simmer.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients for 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 325° on a cookie sheet pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch).
Cool 5 minutes and frost.

title: lentil soup
directions: In a 4 to 6-quart soup pot, boil bones until all the foam can be skimmed from top.
Add vegetables and lentils.
Cook until lentils are soft and soup is thick.
Simmer 2 to 3 hours.
Remove meat from bones and put into soup.
Serve as is or cut sausage up and put in.

title: bess h's christmas salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in one cup hot water.
Cool.
Mix next three ingredients together.
Add to Jell-O.
Stir well.
Add cherries and nuts.

title: chicken in peanut sauce
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan over high heat, bring 2 quarts water to boil.
Add chicken breast halves and reduce heat to low.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes until chicken is cooked through.
Using a slotted spoon, remove chicken to plate.
Return water to boil; add vermicelli and cook 5 to 7 minutes until just tender.

title: canned snap beans
directions: Put sugar, vinegar and salt in a container and cover with water.
Bring to a rolling boil and boil for 4 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.
Then put in boiling water and boil 7 minutes. Remove and untighten tops a little.
To serve, you may cook and season with water in beans if you want a sour taste.
If not, drain, wash in hot water and season.

title: lemon lemon cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Prepare pudding as directed, cooking on stove.
Cool the cake.
Pour the lemon pudding over the cake.
Chill for several hours.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
A lemon lover's delight!

title: oven fried green tomatoes
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, salt and pepper in a shallow dish and set aside.
Slice green tomatoes in 1/2-inch slices.
Dip tomato slices in water; dredge in cornmeal mixture.
Coat baking sheet with vegetable cooking spray.
Coat each slice with spray and place on baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake another 5 minutes or until golden.

title: slush
directions: Make tea with boiling water and tea bags.
Add sugar, orange juice, lemonade, cold water and vodka.
Mix well.
Freeze.
Shave off half glass; fill with Wink, grapefruit juice or Squirt.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Brown pork chops.
Place in baking dish.
Cover completely with sliced potatoes and sliced onions.
Cover with a can of cream of mushroom soup.
Cover dish with foil.
Bake at 325° until chops are tender (45 minutes to 1 hour).
Dot with cheese and return to oven, only to melt cheese.

title: charleston shrimp sandwich
directions: Grind shrimp in food processor.
Mix in all other ingredients and fold in enough mayonnaise to make a paste.
Spread on whole wheat bread and cut diagonally into 4 triangles.
Yields 2 1/2 cups of spread.

title: original chicken noodle soup
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Add to the broth Lawry's Season-All, celery, carrots, salt and pepper.
Cook on medium for 45 minutes.
Add spaghetti and boil for 10 minutes.
Turn down to simmer with lid on for about 30 minutes.

title: marinade for any type of beef
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put desired meat into a plastic bag.
Pour marinade over meat.
Seal.
Refrigerate overnight.	Turn several times.
The longer it is in the refrigerator, the better.
Cook meat on grill or broil in oven.

title: split pea soup
directions: Rinse peas.
Place in large pan or soup pot.
Add water, celery, onion, carrots and bay leaf.
Bring to boil.
Reduce to simmer, cover and cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours until thick.
Add about 1/2 teaspoon sugar and salt to taste.
(Remove any chunks of celery that did not cook down and the bay leaf.)
Ready to serve!

title: thousand island dressing
directions: In blender, put pickle cubes (including juice), coarsely chopped onion, vinegar and sugar.
Blend on medium speed until fine, but not a liquid.
Pour into large bowl.
Add mayonnaise and stir until blended.
Add ketchup until desired color.

title: easy peanut butter fudge
directions: Place butter or margarine in 2-quart saucepan on low heat until butter is melted.
Add peanut butter; stir until creamy. Add the box of powdered sugar; stir until smooth consistency. Spread in a 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Lay Hershey bars on top. Place in oven on warm until Hershey bars are melted.
Remove from oven; spread evenly.
Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: apple gingerbread
directions: Heat oven to 350°F, 180°C or gas mark 4.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together and pack into a 9 x 3 x 5-inch pan or form into two loaves.
Place 4 strips bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: celery with mushrooms and spinach
directions: In a skillet, heat oil and saute garlic.
When slightly brown, add onion and celery.
Stir occasionally.
Cook for 2 minutes. Add green pepper and mushrooms.
Cook for 3 minutes, stirring. Add spinach.
Season with oyster sauce.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Wash peppers; remove seeds, etc.
Cook in 1 cup boiling water for 5 minutes; drain.
(Can microwave with a little water until soft, about 2 minutes.)
Brown beef and onion; stir often.
Drain off any fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put small amount of spaghetti sauce in the bottom of a casserole dish; put in peppers, then the meat mixture.
Add the remaining spaghetti sauce.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: pecan rolls
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well; mix with hands if necessary. Shape mixture into 5 (4 1/2 or 5-inch) rolls.
Mixture will be dry.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Make this casserole 1 day ahead as the flavor intensifies with time.

title: savory beef and vegetable stew
directions: In hot oil in Dutch oven, brown beef cubes well on all sides. Remove and set aside.
Add chopped onions, green peppers and celery to Dutch oven and saute until tender, about 8 minutes.
Return beef to pan.
Add parsley, garlic, tomato sauce, wine, bouillon cubes, salt, pepper, thyme, bay leaf and 2 cups water.
Bring to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 1 1/4 hours.
Add vegetables and simmer, covered, 1 hour longer or until tender.
Remove from heat; skim off fat.
Mix flour with 2 tablespoons cold water and stir into beef mixture.
Arrange tomato wedges, skin side up, on top. Simmer, covered, 10 minutes until slightly thickened.
Makes 6 servings.

title: caramel cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time and beat.
Add flavoring, cake flour, baking powder and salt. Press with hands in pan, 6 x 10-inch about 1/2-inch thick.
Spread over finely chopped nuts (almonds).

title: charcoaled shrimp
directions: Put shrimp in a mixing bowl and pour marinade over them. Marinate for 15 to 20 minutes.
Have charcoal cooker hot and put shrimp on, cooking for only 1 or 2 minutes on each side.
Use tongs for turning.
This dish is a fabulous appetizer, but a great main course with a good salad and au gratin potatoes.

title: banana icebox cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat with spoon until fluffy.
Add flour sifted with soda alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in bananas and pecans.
Makes 3 layers; be sure to grease and flour pans before pouring in batter.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix cucumbers, onions, peppers and salt in a large bowl.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Add vinegar, sugar and celery seed.
Pack cucumbers in jar and pour liquid over.
Keep refrigerated in jars with lids on tight.

title: cracker - snack
directions: Mix oil, dill weed, lemon pepper and Ranch dressing thoroughly and heat extra warm.
Pour over crackers and stir until crackers absorb oil.
Store in sealed jar for 12 hours.

title: islander pork chops
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve syrup.
In large skillet, brown chops in oil.
Add onion and saute until soft.
Drain fat.
Add reserved pineapple syrup and remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Turn chops, cover and simmer 20 minutes longer.
Add pineapple slices and heat through.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add eggs and mix well. Add milk and flour alternately.
Add salt and flavoring.
Mix well.
Bake in greased and floured baking pans at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes or until done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Spread chopped broccoli in long casserole dish.
Spread stuffing on top of broccoli.
Mix mushroom and chicken soups with milk; add melted margarine in saucepan.
Heat (do not boil); put stuffing over broccoli.
Pour soup mixture over stuffing.
Place casserole in oven for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cool whip pie
directions: Mix milk with lemon juice, add pineapple, then Cool Whip and mix well.
Then add nuts and coconut.
Turn into 2 pie shells. This makes 2 pies.
Put in refrigerator until firm.
This will keep for a long time.

title: oven fries
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
With nonstick cooking spray, grease two baking sheets.
In bowl, combine potatoes, oil, parsley, pepper and rosemary; toss.
Place on baking sheets.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, until browned and crisp.
Add salt; toss.
Serves 6.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Combine flour, cream cheese and margarine; mix well.
Separate into 2 rolls.
Roll out until thin.
Sprinkle with sausage and roll up.
Slice off amount desired.
Lay slices on cookie sheet. Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Slices better if put in freezer for a couple hours.

title: orange julia
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender container.
Process until smooth.
Makes about 8 small servings.

title: zucchini supreme
directions: Place melted butter in 9 x 13-inch pan and arrange zucchini, onions, peppers and tomatoes in layers.
Sprinkle bread crumbs, oil, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese over mixture.
Cover with foil and bake 50 to 60 minutes at 375°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions in margarine until tender.
Add broccoli and cook until tender.
Add all other ingredients.
Place in casserole and cook in oven until bubbly.
Top with bread crumbs if desired.

title: beef curry
directions: Heat oil in heavy skillet; saute onion over medium heat just until tender. Stir in curry powder. Cook 1 minute. Add beef cubes and remaining ingredients in order as listed.
Continue cooking until beef cubes are lightly browned.
Add enough boiling water to barely cover beef (about 2 cups).
Cover skillet and simmer gently about 1 1/2 hours or until beef is extremely tender. Thicken with cornstarch and water mixture. Serve with steamed rice. Serves 4 to 6.

title: bread and butter "crisp" pickles
directions: Wash pickles and slice.
Cut up onions. Work in 1/2 cup salt. Let stand for 2 hours. Drain liquid. Add the spices.
Mix vinegar, sugar, cloves and turmeric and bring to a boil.
Simmer (not boil) for a couple of minutes.
Put in jars immediately. Makes 8 pints.

title: spiced prunes
directions: Soak prunes overnight in water.
Add sugar and spices, tied in a cheesecloth bag.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add vinegar; cook 10 minutes longer or until syrup is fairly thick.

title: choco-nut bon-bons
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Roll into small balls (about 150). Place on a cookie sheet and chill.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin over double boiler.
Dip balls into chocolate, using toothpicks.
Place on wax paper to harden.
Refrigerate or freeze.
Easier if you
mix batter with hands.

title: muffins
directions: Mix ingredients in a large bowl and then pour into a muffin pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 17 minutes.

title: peanut butter swirl bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine peanut butter, butter and sugars; beat until creamy.
Gradually beat in eggs and vanilla extract.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt; blend into peanut butter mixture.
Spread into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over surface.
Place in 350° oven for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Run knife through to marbleize.
Return to oven.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes more. Cut into 2 x 1-inch bars.
Makes 4 dozen bars.

title: pineapple pepper chicken
directions: In a saucepan, combine the first 10 ingredients. Stir until smooth. Bring to a boil. Cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened. Set aside. Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the chicken. Brown on all sides. Place in 2 greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dishes. Pour reserved sauce over chicken. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes. Add pineapple and green pepper. Bake 15 minutes longer or until heated through.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and flour together; add water.
Cook until clear in color.
Add lemon juice, grated rind and butter.
Add beaten egg yolks and cook 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue and bake 15 minutes at 300°.
This is for a 9-inch pie.

title: shells and broccoli
directions: Cook pasta.
Meanwhile, saute garlic in olive oil in a large skillet.
Add broccoli with a few tablespoons of pasta water. Cook lightly.
Drain pasta and place on plates.
Top with broccoli. Sprinkle with grated Parmesan.

title: skillet scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes thin.
Put into hot grease in skillet.
Add onion.
Cook until brown and tender; drain grease.
Add cream of mushroom soup.
Add the water.
Stir.
Pat slices of cheese on top of mixture.
Put lid on skillet and simmer until cheese is melted. Stir the mixture again and simmer until done.

title: california blend casserole
directions: Mix together cream of chicken and Miracle Whip, then put in layers in a 9 x 13 pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in a large bowl.
Add nuts, raisins and applesauce.
Add oil last.
Bake in tube, Bundt or loaf pan (10 x 14-inch) in slow oven (325°) for about 1 hour.
I put a small amount of water in pan in oven under cake while baking.
One-half recipe makes a large loaf.
Whole recipe makes 48 cupcakes.
Serve plain or frost lightly.
Keeps well.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal and let stand for 20 minutes. Meanwhile, cream butter and sugars together.
Add vanilla.
Beat eggs well and add to mixture.
Add rest of the ingredients.
Mix well.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Add frozen corn to food processor along with other ingredients.
Blend, leaving a few whole corn kernels.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: cream wafers
directions: Mix thoroughly the butter, cream and flour; cover and chill. Heat oven to 375°.
Roll about 1/3 of dough at a time 1/8-inch thick on floured, cloth covered board.
Keep remaining dough refrigerated until ready to roll.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch circles. Transfer rounds with spatula to piece of waxed paper that is heavily coated with sugar.
Turn each round so that both sides are coated with sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Prick with fork about 4 times.
Bake for 7 to 9 minutes or just until set but not brown.
Cool.
Put cookies together in pairs with Creamy Filling.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Crumble corn bread.
Mix with other ingredients.

title: fresh blueberry cobbler
directions: Melt margarine and place into baking dish.
Place blueberries on top of margarine.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour on top of berries.
I like to add a little extra margarine on top of mix.
Place into heated oven at 325° and bake for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Do not cover when baking.
Be sure dish is large enough so the cobbler will not bubble over into oven.

title: fiesta rice
directions: Saute peppers and onions in oil in a large skillet.
Stir in chili powder, salt and pepper and corn.
Add tomatoes and simmer 5 minutes.
Add bouillon; bring to boil.
Simmer to reduce to your taste.
Serve over rice.

title: savory crescent chicken squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend softened cream cheese and 2 tablespoons margarine until smooth.
Add chicken, salt, pepper, milk, chives or onion and pimento.
Mix well.
Separate rolls into 4 rectangles, seal perforations.
Spoon 1/2 cup chicken mixture onto center of each rectangle. Pull the 4 corners of dough to center of mixture.
Seal opening.
Brush tops with remaining 1 tablespoon margarine.
Dip in crushed croutons.
(Coat all sides and bottom with crushed croutons.)
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.
Serves 4.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Crust:
Unroll and press dough onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 10 to 15 minutes until nicely brown.
Cool.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Layer bread and cheese in greased casserole.
Put tomatoes, bacon and mushrooms on top.
Mix eggs, milk, mustard, salt, pepper and onion powder.
Pour over casserole.
Chill 24 hours.
Cover with tent of aluminum foil.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: velveeta salsa dip
directions: Microwave cubed Velveeta and salsa in a 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe bowl on High for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Press sugar, butter and crackers into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix ice cream, pudding and milk.
Pour into pan over crackers.
Pour large Cool Whip over ice cream mix.
Top with crushed crackers. Chill and serve.

title: hamburger dip
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients and drain.
Add next 4 ingredients. Simmer 30 to 45 minutes and add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Serve in a chafing dish with Mexican (tostados) chips.

title: mom's pineapple cheese pie
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients on low heat until thickened.
Put aside.
Cream the cream cheese with 1/2 cup sugar, vanilla, salt and eggs (add one at a time).
When creamed together, add milk, beating slowly.
Once mixed in, add pineapple mixture and mix by hand.
Then add to crust and bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 50 minutes or until top is nice and brown.

title: broccoli casserole
