directions: Cook broccoli and drain well.
Place broccoli on flat 8 1/2 x 11 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch Pyrex dish.
Mix all other ingredients except crackers and pour over broccoli.
Mix well.
Melt 1 stick margarine.
Mix in cracker crumbs and sprinkle atop casserole. Bake for 30 minutes on 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: special sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix first three ingredients:
sweet potatoes, margarine and sugar.
Then beat in eggs and milk.
Pour into a 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole.

title: peachy cream pie
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients at medium speed for 2 minutes and pour into greased pie plate.
Place sliced peaches on top.
Cream together in a small bowl for 2 minutes, cream cheese, peach juice and 1/2 cup sugar.
Spoon over peaches, leaving 1-inch bare outside edge.
Combine 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until crust is golden brown.
Topping will be soft until cool.
Store any leftovers in refrigerator.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Lay shrimp in pan.
Pour butter over and squeeze lemon juice over.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake shrimp for 2 minutes.
Turn over; add slices of lemon with rind and bake for another 2 minutes.

title: stewed peaches
directions: Cook slowly until thick or pie consistency.
Good substitute for dried peaches.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: In baking dish, combine rice, chicken, soup and water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until chicken is no longer pink and juices run clear.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lemon squares
directions: In a bowl, blend together 1 cup of the flour, the butter and 1/4 cup of the confectioners sugar until the mixture resembles meal.
Pat the mixture into an 8-inch square baking pan and bake it in the middle of a preheated 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until it is a pale golden.

title: lovelight chocolate cake
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Gradually beat in 1/2 cup of the sugar.
Continue beating until stiff and glossy enough to stand in peaks.
Sift remaining sugar, flour, soda and salt into another bowl.
Pour in oil and half the buttermilk.
Beat 1 minute at medium speed.
Scrape sides and bottom of bowl constantly.
Add remaining buttermilk, egg yolks and chocolate.
Beat 1 minute more.
Fold meringue into batter by cutting down gently through batter, across the bottom, up and over, turning bowl often.
Pour into greased and floured cake pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: white sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Add flour; blend.
Add milk, stirring constantly.
Cook until thick and smooth.
Add salt and pepper.
Cover and cook 5 to 8 minutes.
Makes 1 cup sauce.

title: doritos dip
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage in pan; drain.
Melt cheese in double boiler . Mix cheese, hamburger and sausage together.
Add onion, peppers and tomato; stir until smooth.
Serve warm with Doritos chips.

title: egg rolls
directions: Grind all meat.
Chop chestnuts and mushrooms.
Mix meat, chestnuts, mushrooms, salt and pepper in a large bowl.
Fry cabbage, carrots and green onions for about 3 minutes.
Remove and mix with meat mixture.
Place a tablespoon of meat mixture on each lumpia wrapper and roll.
Deep fry on medium heat, turning constantly, until golden brown.
Drain on rack.
Serve.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix with creamed mixture.
Add chocolate chips, Hershey bar and nuts.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet.
Make golf-ball size cookies.
Place 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 6 minutes.
Makes 112 cookies.

title: martin's fruit nut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees. Lightly grease a large cookie sheet. In a large mixing bowl, cream together the butter and sugar. Add the eggs and beat well. Heat the cherry juice and stir the baking soda into it. Mixture will foam. Add to the creamed mixture and mix. In medium bowl, combine flour, cinnamon, cloves and pecan meal. Stir to mix. Add to the creamed mixture and mix well.
Stir in the pecans, dates, and cherries. Drop from a teaspoon onto cookie sheet. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until the cookies are lightly browned.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: jonny marzetti
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Cook noodles and drain.
Combine beef with noodles and both cans of soup.
Cut cheese into squares and stir into mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot sausage
directions: In a large bowl combine all ingredients, blending thoroughly. Let mixture stand for 20 minutes to allow flavors to blend.

title: cream cheese tarts
directions: Soften butter and cream cheese to room temperature.
Blend thoroughly and add flour to make soft dough.
Chill in refrigerator 1/2 hour.
Roll out 1/3 of dough at one time.
Cut into 2-inch squares and put a "spot" of jelly on each square. Fold over four corners to seal.

title: vegetable chowder
directions: Melt margarine in Dutch oven over medium heat.
Add onion and garlic; cook until transparent.
Add celery, bouillon, potatoes, tomatoes, corn, carrots, salt, thyme and celery seed.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir together cornstarch and water until smooth.
Add to soup.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.

title: apple cheese casserole
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Mix cheese and flour into creamed mixture.
In a buttered casserole, put one can of pie apples.
Pour combined mixture on top of apples and spread to cover apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Use either a one or one and a half quart dish.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Boil Jell-O, sugar and water to dissolve.
Remove from heat. Stir in the apricot baby food and pineapple.
Cool.
Fold in Eagle Brand milk and cream cheese.
Chill until firm.

title: baking hen sauce and eggplant
directions: In saucepan, brown baking hens 2 minutes in olive oil with onion and garlic.
Add pureed tomatoes and all seasoning except sugar.
Place large pepper (whole) in sauce and let cook for 1 hour or more.
Do not let pepper break.
Add mushrooms and sugar; cook for another 20 minutes.
Remove pepper from sauce.
Soak eggplant in cold water several times; drain and squeeze dry.
Heat oil and put eggplant in mixture of egg, milk, salt, pepper, cheese and then in flour and bread crumbs mixture.
Fry lightly on both sides and place on platter.
In baking dish, add layers of rigatoni macaroni, sauce, eggplant and cheese.
Bake in 325° oven for 3/4 hour.
Only use half of the cheese in egg mixture and half when making layers.
You may top this with Mozzarella cheese before baking.
Baking hen is served as a side dish or deboned and placed in baking dish with layers of eggplant and macaroni.

title: rutabagas
directions: Wash, pare and dice rutabagas in tiny squares.
Add salt, pepper, onion and enough water to cover.
Boil 25 to 30 minutes. Drain water.
Sprinkle with sugar and paprika.
Add butter and parsley.
Steam 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Place cream cheese in medium-size microwave-safe bowl. Microwave at Medium power until softened for 1 to 2 minutes, stirring once.
Shred crabmeat; stir into cream cheese with remaining ingredients.
Microwave on Medium until dip is heated through, 4 to 7 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers or party rye bread slices.
Makes 2 cups.

title: spicy pasta pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch pie plate or 13 x 9 x 2-inch rectangular baking pan; set aside.
In 10-inch skillet over medium flame, cook tomatoes, onions, mushrooms and peppers.
Stir in spaghetti sauce; set aside.
In large bowl, combine 1/4 cup of Parmesan cheese, 1 egg and margarine.
Add hot spaghetti; toss to mix well.
Spread spaghetti mixture on bottom and up side of prepared pie plate, making 1/2-inch rim.
In small bowl, combine Ricotta, parsley, remaining egg and remaining 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Spread mixture over bottom of crust.
Top with vegetable mixture.
Bake 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 5 minutes more or until cheese melts.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut into wedges.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Break spaghetti into 1-inch pieces.
Cook and then drain. Don't overcook.
Remember, you will be baking in oven for additional cooking time.
Saute mushrooms in butter then remove the skin and bones from the cooked chicken breasts.
Next, cut chicken into large bite-sized pieces and mix with the sauteed mushrooms and mix with the remaining ingredients, EXCEPT PARMESAN.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Boil sweet potatoes 20 minutes or longer until done.
Place them in a large mixing bowl and add butter, sugar and eggs.
Beat slowly.
Add milk and extracts; stir until firm and pour in 3 (9-inch) pastry shells.
Bake 30 minutes.
(You can use 2 deep dish pie shells.)

title: mystery pecan pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, 1/3 c. sugar, 1 egg, 1 tsp. vanilla and salt in small mixing bowl until thick & creamy;
Set aside.
Beat remaining eggs until just blended;
Add remaining sugar, vanilla, and corn syrup.
Spread cream cheese mixture in bottom of pie shell.
Sprinkle w/pecans;
Gently pour corn syrup mixture over pecans.
Bake in 375° gas oven 35 to 40 minutes or until center is firm to touch.
Cream cheese will rise under pecans as it cooks.

title: crusty eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant, if you wish.
Cut in 1/2-inch slices.
In shallow pan, beat eggs slightly.
In another pan, combine cheese, bread crumbs, parsley, salt and pepper.
Dust each eggplant slice with flour.
Dip in eggs to coat all over and dredge in crumb mixture, shaking off excess.
Pour 2 tablespoons of butter in each of 2 jelly roll pans; tip to coat evenly.
Arrange eggplant slices in butter.
Bake, uncovered, in a 400° oven for 25 minutes, turning once to brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy refrigerator rolls
directions: Heat milk, sugar and Crisco and stir to melt Crisco.
Cool to 105° to 110°.
Add 1 package yeast and stir to dissolve (about 5 minutes).
Add enough flour to make a thin batter (about 2 cups). Cover and let stand in a warm place for 2 hours.
Add salt, baking powder, soda and enough flour to make dough not sticky, but the right consistency to knead (about 4 cups).
It is not necessary to knead this dough, but beat it while adding the flour.
Place dough in refrigerator, covered, overnight.
Roll out on floured board or wax paper.
Cut rounds with biscuit cutter, dip in melted butter, fold over and place on cookie sheet.
Cover and let rise 2 1/2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 60 rolls.

title: iced cappuccino(diabetic)
directions: Place all ingredients in food processor or blender and process until smooth.
Place container in freezer 1 to 2 hours.
Scrape sides of container; process until smooth and frothy.
Garnish as desired.
Serve immediately.
Makes 2 servings.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and cook on medium until hard boil. Test in cold water for hard ball.
Remove from heat immediately and add peanut butter.
(For chocolate fudge, add 3 tablespoons cocoa.)
Beat a while; it doesn't take long before it's too hard to spread.
Have greased dish ready.

title: italian bean and sausage stew
directions: Cook sausage in 12-inch skillet over medium heat until lightly browned, about 4 minutes.
Add onions and garlic; cook until sausage is no longer pink.
Pour off fat.
Add tomatoes, beans, picante sauce, basil and oregano.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Add green pepper, zucchini and cornstarch mixture; continue to simmer 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender and sauce is thickened.
Sprinkle with cheese and serve with additional picante sauce.
Makes about eight 1/2 cups.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce in bottom of bowl.
Layer remaining ingredients, layering bacon bits on top of salad.

title: lush lime cooler beverage
directions: Place 1 cup lime sherbet and limeade in blender container; cover.
Blend until well combined.
Add milk; blend.
Pour into glasses.
Top with a scoop of sherbet.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients together, then add milk and the beaten egg yolks and cook until thick.
Then add butter and vanilla.
Then pour into the already baked pie shell.
(Stir constantly while cooking.)

title: easy cocoa mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart airtight container.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Cover raisins with boiling water and cook 5 minutes; drain, reserving juice.
Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs; beat until smooth.
Sift flour, salt, soda and spices.
Mix with oatmeal.
Add to first mixture alternately with raisin liquid.
Add fruit and nuts.

title: cheese muffins
directions: Measure flour; add baking powder, sugar and salt.
Sift again. Combine egg and milk and add all at once to flour mixture.
Add shortening.
Stir until dry ingredients are dampened (batter will be lumpy).
Add cheese.
Spoon into greased muffin pans, filling each 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook sugar, butter, cocoa, milk and vanilla over high heat. After coming to a full boil, cook for 1 1/2 minutes.
Add oats and peanut butter.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: spinach and fish delight
directions: Place fish in bottom of microwavable casserole dish; layer the spinach on top.
Layer sliced or shredded Muenster on top.
Cover lightly.
Microwave on High until fish is done (flaky), approximately 7 minutes for fresh fish and approximately 12 minutes for frozen fish.
You may alter this recipe to suit your taste!

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onion and carrots for 5 minutes.
Melt oleo and mix with stuffing mix.
Combine all other ingredients and alternate the squash mixture with the stuffing mix.
End with stuffing.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: twinkie cake
directions: In a pie pan, cover bottom with the sliced Twinkies.
Spread strawberry pie filling over the Twinkies.
Mix together the sliced bananas and crushed pineapple in a separate bowl; the pineapple juice prevents the bananas from turning brown.
Spread this mixture over the strawberry pie filling.
Next, spread Cool Whip over the bananas.
Use a potato peeler to shave the chocolate bar on top of the Cool Whip.
Also, decorate with the nuts and cherries.
Cool in refrigerator at least 30 minutes.

title: peach yum-yum
directions: Mix graham crackers and butter and set aside.
Mix Dream Whip according to directions on box.
Add cream cheese and sugar; mix on high.

title: cocoa pudding
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, and flour.
Add well beaten eggs, beat well.
Add milk and margarine.
Pour in greased pan using margarine.
Bake at 350 degrees, stirring 2 or 3 times while cooking, approximately 35 minutes.
I not smooth, I beat with hand mixer.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash and all other ingredients together.
Pour into a greased baking dish. Bake in preheated 375° oven for 40 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan.
Let simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Combine all ingredients except peaches and margarine in a baking dish. Pour peaches on top of mixture, then slice butter on top of peaches.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: quick corn chowder
directions: Mix together and heat.
Can serve right away!

title: yummy cheesecake
directions: Make a graham cracker crust and press into 10-inch spring-form pan (halfway up sides).
Mix with electric mixer cream and Ricotta cheeses, add sugar gradually.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, then cornstarch.
Mix well.
Add 1 at a time vanilla, lemon and butter.
Mix well until smooth and creamy.
Fold in sour cream by hand.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour (lightly browned).
Shut off heat and leave in oven 2 more hours.
Leave covered in fridge (in pan).
Take off sides and serve (16 to 18 pieces).

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain.
In saucepan, melt 1 stick margarine and Velveeta.
Mix with broccoli and pour into baking dish.
Melt remaining stick of margarine and then add corn flake crumbs.
Sprinkle on top of broccoli/cheese mix.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Stir all ingredients together by hand, blending thoroughly.

title: cinnamon biscuits
directions: Bowl One:
Dip biscuits in melted butter.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients except cheese. Place in a lightly greased casserole dish. Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 30 minutes. Sprinkle cheese over top and return to oven for 15 minutes or until center is firm.

title: cheerios treats
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Microwave margarine or spread in large microwavable bowl on High 45 seconds or until melted.
Add marshmallows, toss to coat with margarine or spread.
Microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth when stirred, 45 seconds. Stir in peanut butter.
Add cereal quickly. Mix lightly until coated.
Makes 24.

title: korean beef
directions: Stir together all ingredients.
Pour over steak that has been cut into 1-inch cubes.
Marinate in refrigerator overnight. Drain.
Cook by stir-frying.
Do not overcook.

title: fruit soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Cook on low heat for 8 to 10 hours.
Remove lemon slices and cinnamon stick.

title: yeast bread
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in sugar, salt and liquid fat.
Cool to lukewarm.
Measure into bowl the warm water.
Sprinkle in yeast. Stir until dissolved.
Add egg, beaten, then sifted flour.
Beat. Knead.
Place in a greased bowl.
Cover with wax paper or foil. Let double size.
Punch down.
Place in refrigerator.
Remove later.
Rise.
Roll out.
Cut into shapes.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in 425° oven.

title: aunt dusty's apple dapple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except fruit.
Blend well.
Fold in fruit and nuts.
Bake in tube pan or 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 60 to 80 minutes.
Tastes better on the second day.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and margarine.
Add a few drops of water, if needed.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix powdered sugar, 2 eggs and cream cheese.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: broiled basil tomatoes
directions: About 15 minutes before serving, preheat broiler if manufacturer directs.
Cut out stem of each tomato and then cut each tomato horizontally in half.
Place halves, cut sides up, on rack in broiling pan.
Brush with oil.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and basil leaves.
About 5 to 7 inches from source of heat, broil tomato halves until tomatoes are heated through, about 10 minutes. Makes 4 servings, about 50 calories per serving.

title: pistachio harvest salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss this with the first mixture.
Let marinate overnight in icebox.

title: maple syrup
directions: Slowly heat corn syrup and brown sugar.
Heat until brown sugar dissolves.
Remove from heat.
Add maple flavoring to taste and 2 tablespoons butter.

title: brown bag apple pear pie
directions: You will also need 1 large brown paper bag.

title: spinach salad with hot bacon dressing
directions: With scissors, snip spinach coarsely into a salad bowl.
Cook diced bacon in a skillet over moderately high heat (about 325°) until crisp.
Reduce heat to moderate (about 250°).
Add sugar, green onions, salt, vinegar, mustard and paprika.
Bring to the boiling point and remove from heat.
Just before serving, pour the hot dressing over the spinach and toss lightly until leaves are coated.
Serves 4.

title: nick's chili
directions: In large saucepan, heat oil (or spray with Pam before heating) and saute meat.
Add onion, peppers, chilies, garlic, spices and salt.
Add chocolate, tomato paste, whole tomatoes, beer and 1/2 cup water.
Add beans.
Bring to boil, lower heat.
Cook 1 hour, uncovered.

title: arla's fudge
directions: In a blender or bowl mix together powdered sugar and eggs. In a double boiler melt and blend well the chocolate chips and margarine.
Add this to the sugar/egg mixture.
Add nuts.
Pour into sprayed 9 x 11 inch glass dish.
Refrigerate for 4 hours. Cut into squares and enjoy.

title: cornmeal mush
directions: Bring to a boil 5 cups water and salt. Combine corn meal and 2 cups cold water. Stir into boiling water. Cook for 30 minutes on low heat, stirring frequently. Serve hot with milk and sugar or pour into loaf pan to cool and set.
Slice, dust with flour, if desired, and fry in well-greased skillet.

title: sunshine, hi ho apple pie(no apples required)
directions: Bring sugar and cream of tartar and water to rolling boil. Add crackers and boil 2 minutes.
Do not stir; add spice.
Put pie in unbaked pie shell and bake until brown.

title: holiday salad
directions: Mix together and chill thoroughly.

title: country time pralines
directions: Cook milk and sugar until soft ball forms in a cup of cold water. Remove the mixture from stove.
Add margarine and vanilla to the sugar and milk mixture.
Stir until the margarine melts. Add pecans. Beat until cooled and the mixture loses its shine. Drop by spoonfuls on to tin foil.
Let the pralines cool completely before serving.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry (Pillsbury Ready Crust). Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in pie plate.
Slightly beat eggs.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour cream mixture into pie plate.
Bake for 15 minutes at 425°.
Bake for 30 minutes longer at 300° or until knife comes clean when inserted 1-inch from edge. Let stand for 10 minutes before cutting.

title: cherry congealed salad
directions: Mix cherry pie filling, 1 can Eagle Brand milk, Cool Whip and nuts.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in large casserole dish.
Bake 35 minutes. Sprinkle onion rings on top just before baking time is up.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain all canned ingredients and the pimientos.
Mix all together.
Place in tightly covered container.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve cold.
Makes large bowl.

title: stale cookies
directions: If cookies dry out or harden, put a piece of bread in the cookie tin with the cookies to freshen them.
Works great! Replace bread as needed.

title: mushrooms and shrimp on toast
directions: Tip: Marinate the shrimp in 2 tablespoons of lemon juice and 3 tablespoons oil for 30 minutes before assembling.

title: wild rice and sausage casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, flour, flavoring, meal and milk.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Sift
flour
3 times with salt.
Add alternately with sour
cream
to
which soda has been added.
Fold in stiffly beaten
egg
whites
and flavorings. Put batter in greased and
lightly
floured
tube pan and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: papa's crockpot macaroni & cheese
directions: Grease crockpot with 2 tbsp shortening.
Cook macaroni according to package directions and drain.
Combine with evaporated milk, milk, eggs, shredded cheese, margarine, salt and pepper in large bowl.
Mix well.
Spoon into greased crockpot. Cover with cheese slices.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and cook on low for 3-4 hours.
Yields 10 servings.

title: ting-a-lings
directions: Melt chocolate bits.
Cool to room temperature.
Stir in cereal until well coated.
Drop by tablespoons onto wax paper. Let set about 2 hours.
May need to refrigerate to set.

title: pork chops with scalloped potatoes
directions: I precook my potatoes for about 10 minutes and drain.
In a saucepan, melt butter; stir in flour, salt, pepper and onion.
Add chicken broth gradually and stir constantly until mixture boils. Cook for 1 minute.
Remove and pour mixture over potatoes and mix well carefully.
Brown pork chops in oil and season to taste. Spread potatoes in a greased baking dish or pan.
Place pork chops on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer or until potatoes are tender.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: english muffin delight
directions: Put a slice of tomato on top of English muffin.
Sprinkle with sharp Cheddar cheese.
Put in the oven at 350° until cheese melts all over.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into a greased 10-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie shell and set aside to cool.
Mix sugar, water, cornstarch, jello and food coloring.
Cook until thick and clear, stirring frequently.
Cool.
Fold in strawberries; pour in pie crust and chill.
Serve plain or topped with whipped cream.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Combine brown sugar, oleo and eggs.
In buttermilk dissolve soda.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Heat oven to 325°.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased baking sheet and bake for 15 minutes.

title: welsh cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients and shortening.
Add egg and enough milk (3/4 cup) to make a little more wet.
Thaw pie crust.
Mix in other ingredients.
Roll on floured surface about 1/4 inch thick. Cook on griddle or electric fry pan until light brown on both sides.
Very good.

title: brides pink punch
directions: Mix 1 cup boiling water with one package gelatin; let cool (do not let gel).
Mix with the cooled gelatin the following ingredients:
drink mix, sugar, water and pineapple juice.
Chill in refrigerator.
When ready to serve, add chilled 7-Up and pineapple sherbet.

title: "apple delite"(camp fire desserts)
directions: You will also need heavy-duty aluminum foil.

title: turkey and ham pinwheels
directions: Blend cream cheese, onion, horseradish and Worcestershire sauce until smooth and spreadable.
Separate slices of ham and turkey, laying one slice of turkey on each slice of ham and then spread with cheese mixture.
Roll and fasten with toothpicks. Chill.
Just before serving, slice into 1/2-inch
slices.
Makes approximately 50 pinwheels. Double recipe for larger parties.

title: apricot salad
directions: Save the juice and mix 1 cup pineapple and apricot juice together.
Mix jello, boiling water, apricots, crushed pineapple and marshmallows together.
When this is firm, top with the pineapple and apricot juice, mixed.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix together and put in baking dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chips in double boiler.
Water should be just warm enough to melt chips.
Leave top pan in water after removing from heat. Pour in peanuts.
Drop on wax paper.
Make whatever size you want. Use more or less peanuts according to how much chocolate you want around the peanuts.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix spinach, cream of potato soup and beaten eggs.
Put in a 2-quart greased baking dish.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken breasts with artichoke hearts
directions: Rinse and drain artichoke hearts.
Place in buttered casserole.
Mix soup, wine, salt and pepper, being careful not to oversalt.
Pour over artichoke hearts. Cover with stuffing and dot with butter. Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove foil and continue baking until brown, approximately 30 minutes.

title: spicy carrots
directions: Clean and slice carrots.
Cook until crisp-tender and drain. Melt butter; add brown sugar and orange juice and mix thoroughly. Add carrots and cinnamon; cook 5 minutes.

title: cheese salsa nacho dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in casserole.
Microwave until smooth.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: scotch short bread
directions: Mix butter and sugar by hand.
Gradually add flour until flour is absorbed.
Pat out on cookie sheet (about 11 x 14-inch).
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes to 1 hour until lightly browned. (Prick with fork before baking.) Cut in squares immediately after baking.
Can be cut in shapes beforehand if you add more flour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed; drain and add butter and cheese. Mix until cheese and butter melt.
Put in casserole.
Spread crackers on top.
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: icebox cake
directions: Layer bottom of glass dish with graham crackers.
Make pudding as directed on box.
Layer pudding, graham crackers, pudding, graham crackers, etc.
Place vanilla pudding about middle layer. Put in refrigerator.
Ready to eat anytime.

title: bread spread
directions: Combine butter, paprika, and celery seed. Spread on one side of bread slices. Place on cookie sheet and toast under broiler until browned. This will work with wheat, white or french bread. It is especially good with spaghetti.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well.
Shape into ball.
Can roll in pecans, parsley or paprika.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed. Drain. Rinse with cold water and drain again.

title: "mexican macaroni"
directions: Brown sausage, breaking it up as you fry it.
Drain.
Transfer to a large kettle.
Add all ingredients except cheese slices and cheese from macaroni kit.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, until macaroni is done.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese from kit.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with cheese slices.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° until cheese melts, usually 6 to 8 minutes.

title: pasta with broccoli and pepperoni
directions: Melt butter in big frying pan at medium heat.
Add cut up pepperoni and steamed broccoli.
Stir until heated through.
Pour over hot, cooked pasta.
Sprinkle 1 cup Parmesan on and toss thoroughly.
Mix in vinegar and garlic salt. Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve hot.
Pass additional Parmesan.

title: snax cracker mix(welcome school's)
directions: Place all but crackers in Tupperware quick shake container. Shake until well blended.

title: sinful salad
directions: Mix jello and water.
Add pecans, pineapple, bananas and strawberries (drained well).
Mix well.
Congeal 1/2 mixture and leave 1/2 at room temperature.
Layer 1 cup sour cream over congealed layer.
Pour remaining mixture over sour cream and congeal.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Using low heat,
place chicken on rack.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and meat tenderizer on chicken.
Barbecue until tender. Spread sauce on
chicken;
grill approximately 1 minute.
Turn chicken; spread sauce.
Grill approximately 1 minute.

title: chewy brownies
directions: Microwave sugar, butter and water in large microwave-safe bowl on High for 3 minutes, stirring once. Add chocolate.
Stir until melted.
Stir in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and mix well. Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for about 20 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour oil into a 9 x 13-inch pan; tilt and cover bottom and sides with oil.
Put in cake mix and add water and eggs.
Stir with a fork until blended.
Scrape sides and spread batter evenly over pan.
Spoon in pie filling onto batter.
Stir just enough to give a marbled look.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut and serve.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks.
Stir in milk and lemon juice.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Cool and chill.
Spread whipped cream over pie.
Serve.

title: potato casserole
directions: Place thawed potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix the next 6 ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Top with crushed corn flakes and drizzle with additional stick of oleo.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves approximately 12 people.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush the cookies in plastic bag with rolling pin.
Mix the oleo and cream cheese.
Mix the milk and pudding.
Combine with cream cheese.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Place 1/2 cookie mixture in bottom of pan.
Fill with filling and the other 1/2 of cookie mixture on top.

title: florida key lime pie
directions: Separate eggs carefully.
Blend egg whites with milk.
Slowly add juice.
Pour in pie shell.
Top with whipped cream or meringue.
If use meringue, brown slightly in oven.
Serve chilled.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Combine lemon rind, cloves, sugar and water.
Heat to boiling point and cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Cool and add orange juice concentrate.
Mix well.
Chill.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: In large pan, cook pasta until almost done.
Melt butter in skillet and add onions, mushrooms and chicken.
Cook until onions are transparent.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook and drain ground beef.
Place 1/2 thinly sliced potatoes, 1/2 onion and 1/2 beef in baking dish.
Repeat.
Mix soup with 1 can of water.
Pour over mixture.
Cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and put grated cheese on top.
Place in oven until cheese is lightly browned.

title: potato skins
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Cut potatoes into 8 pieces; place, skin side up, onto cookie sheet.
Brush with vegetable oil; sprinkle with dry mixture.
Broil at 550° for 10 minutes.
Turn over, brush with oil and sprinkle rest of dry mixture.
Broil for 5 more minutes.

title: amish bread pudding
directions: In small saucepan combine milk and butter; stir until butter is melted.
Cool to lukewarm.
Combine eggs, sugar, salt and nutmeg.
Beat at medium speed 1 minute.
Stir in milk mixture. Place bread pieces in a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with raisins.
Add milk mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until mixture is set.
Serve warm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: refrigerator sweet pickles
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, salt, turmeric, celery seed and mustard seed in large jar.
Shake, covered, until sugar and salt are dissolved.
Pack cucumber slices and onion slices into sterilized jars.
Add vinegar mixture.
Chill in refrigerator for 5 days before serving.
Store in refrigerator.
Yield:
20 servings.

title: stuffed zucchini squash
directions: Wash squash; cut off ends, don't pare.
Cool in boiling salted water 5 minutes.
Halve lengthwise; remove pulp with spoon. Combine pulp, bread crumbs, cheese, onion, parsley, salt, pepper, garlic powder and eggs.
Fill shells, dot with butter, sprinkle additional cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: walnut chews(cookies)
directions: Sift the flour, soda and salt.
Cream well the margarine, brown sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add flour mixture; stir in the walnuts and Special K.
Drop by tablespoonfuls.
Bake until golden, for 10 minutes at 350°.
Yields 1 1/2 dozen.

title: hot fruit salad
directions: Combine in a saucepan the butter, flour, sugar and pineapple juice.
Heat until it is hot and thick.
Mix with the fruit and top with the Cheddar cheese and almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix wild rice according to directions on box.
Add mushrooms and pour into a large baking dish.
Place chicken pieces on top.
Dot with butter.
Cover lightly with aluminum foil and bake for 1 hour.

title: green tomato relish(catsup)
directions: Mix the tomatoes, cabbage, peppers and onion.
Add the salt and 1 quart water.
Stir and let stand overnight.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook hen until tender and cube.
Cook butter, flour and milk to	soft sauce, stirring constantly.
Cube cheese, add to undiluted soup;
simmer
until
cheese
melts.
Bring
to boil diced celery,
diced
onion
and
water; cook until tender and then drain.
Mix all ingredients together in a large pan.
Add spaghetti and
mix	well.
Grease
a
roaster
with butter and sprinkle with
crumbled crackers.
Pour in well mixed ingredients and sprinkle
top
with
more cracker crumbs.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
If desired, let stand in refrigerator overnight before baking.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Grind onions and peppers.
Add hamburger, uncooked rice, cracker crumbs, tomato puree and salt to taste.
Make into balls. Roll in flour.
Brown in butter in a pan that has a lid that fits well.
Fill pan 1/2 full with water and let simmer for an hour over a very low flame.
The rice bursts out of the balls, giving the appearance of porcupine.
Garnish with the tomato puree.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into pie shell.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread bean dip in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix taco sauce, sour cream and mayonnaise; spread on top of bean dip. Sprinkle chopped tomato and pepper over mixture.
Sprinkle cheese over tomato and pepper.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: noodles romano
directions: Combine soft butter and basil.
Blend in cream cheese and pepper.
Stir in boiling water and blend well.
Cook noodles according to directions.

title: sweet and sour pork(yield:  4-6 servings)
directions: 1. Cube pork into 1/2-inch chunks.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift flour and cut in shortening. Dissolve yeast in water and combine with milk.
Add yeast mixture to dry ingredients and stir well.
Knead; add flour if needed.
Roll out on floured board 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 450° until brown.
You can pinch off and bake in muffin tins.

title: mom's chicken pie
directions: Layer chicken, onion and eggs in large casserole dish.
Mix all other ingredients.
Pour over chicken.

title: fish and chip bake
directions: Mix potatoes, sour cream, spinach and pepper.
Turn into 10 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into crust.
Chill before serving.

title: creme brulee
directions: Combine pudding mix and cream in medium saucepan; blend well. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil. Remove from heat.
Stir small amount of hot mixture into eggs, mixing well.
Return egg mixture to remaining hot mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook over low heat for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Add vanilla and pour into shallow 1 1/2 quart baking dish.
Chill at least 3 hours.
Evenly sprinkle brown sugar over top of pudding. Broil until sugar melts, about 1 1/2 minutes.
Serve warm or chill.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Work sugar, salt and shortening into potatoes.
Work in 2 1/2 cups of flour.
Reserve 1/2 cup flour to pat out biscuits.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: chicken casserole with saffron rice
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Rinse chicken pieces and pat dry.
Heat the oil in a large casserole and brown, a few chicken pieces at a time. Reserve.
Saute the garlic, onion and green pepper until soft, about 5 minutes.
Add the rice and stir to coat.
Cook over moderate heat until golden, about 3 minutes.
Return the chicken pieces to the casserole.
Stir in the ham, oregano, salt, pepper, saffron, tomatoes and water.
Bring to a boil on top of the stove. Cover and place in the oven for 30 minutes.
Reduce the heat to 250°.
Add the peas, olives and capers.
Continue baking uncovered until chicken is tender, about 20 minutes.
Garnish with parsley and pimento.
Serves 8.

title: maple custard
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into small custard cups.
Set them in a pan of hot water and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, or until the blade of a table knife inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, put sugar and flour.
In saucepan, put oleo, shortening, cocoa and Coca-Cola.
Bring to boil and pour over sugar and flour.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda, vanilla and marshmallows.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: jane's dip
directions: Mix together and chill.
May be used as salad dressing.

title: almond crunch
directions: Line large cookie sheet with foil.
Cover sheet with whole graham cookies; sprinkle with sliced almonds. Melt butter and add sugar. Cook over low heat until mixture begins to thicken.
Spoon over almonds and crackers. Place in 350° oven for 15 minutes. Cool and break into cookie size pieces.
Watch closely; easy to burn.

title: french chicken
directions: Place chicken in small microwave-safe bowl.
Dissolve chicken soup in water.
Pour over chicken.
Add paprika, garlic powder and ground ginger.
Cover; microwave on High for about 5 minutes.

title: hash brown vegetables
directions: Heat oil in large frypan.
Brown potatoes; add onions, then squash, cabbage, salt and pepper.
Cook until tender.

title: quick potato saute
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add onion. Cover; cook for 4 minutes.
Peel potatoes; cut in slices 1/2-inch thick.
Add to pan with butter and savory; season well.
Cook potatoes for 15 minutes over medium-high heat, stirring as needed. Sprinkle with parsley and serve.

title: banana wheat germ muffins
directions: In a large bowl mix the flour, wheat germ, baking powder and baking soda.
In a separate bowl, cream the butter.
Beat in honey, egg, orange juice and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients. Stir in banana, walnut and orange rind.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Make 12 muffins.

title: texas fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pepper to taste. Bake in small bread pan or glass dish at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter french toast
directions: Spread peanut butter between 2 slices of bread.
Beat eggs, milk and seasonings together.
Dip bread into egg mixture and brown in buttered skillet.
Serve with syrup.
Makes 4 servings.

title: best ever lemon meringue pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Combine 1 1/2 cups of sugar, cornstarch and salt, set aside. Combine 4 egg yolks, water and lemon juice, stir into sugar mixture. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until the mixture thickens and boils. boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and stir in butter and grated lemon peel. Spoon into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Beat 4 egg whites and cream of tartar at high speed with an electric mixer until foamy. Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar, one tablespoon at a time, until stiff peaks form. Add vanilla; beating well. Spread over the pie, sealing to the edge. Bake for 25 to 28 minutes.

title: buttermilk cheese bread(for auto bread baker)
directions: Pour in all ingredients in the order listed.
Select white bread and push "Start."

title: sandy's zucchini bread
directions: Mix zucchini, eggs, oil and water; blend in dry ingredients. Pour into greased and floured pans and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 3 loaves or 1 large 9 x 13-inch pan. Glaze to your liking and cool well before slicing.
Freeze zucchini in 2-cup servings and make bread all year long.

title: beau monde dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Eat with bread or crackers.

title: pepperoni treats
directions: Add salad dressing gradually.
Use about a teaspoonful and place on each Triscuit crackers.
Broil 3 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding and nuts together.
Add pineapple and marshmallows; mix together.
Add Cool Whip very carefully.
Chill. This is better when left in the fridge for a couple of days!

title: willie's zesty sauce
directions: Brown meat and vegetables.
Drain excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients, alternating water as needed.
Simmer for 1 hour and 30 minutes, stirring occasionally so sauce does not stick.
Serve with your choice of spaghetti or noodles.
Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: kaye's candy
directions: Boil sugar and butter together until it comes to caramel stage.
Spread chopped pecans together on a cookie sheet.
Pour butter and sugar mixture over pecans.
Take 2 Hershey bars and lay on top until melted, then spread with a knife.
Cool.
Break into pieces and store in sealed container.

title: frosted brownies
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt in a bowl.
Combine 1/2 cup margarine, shortening, water and 1/4 cup cocoa in saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Pour into flour mixture.
Add 1/2 cup of buttermilk, eggs, soda and 1 teaspoon of vanilla; mix well. Spread batter in greased 16 x 11 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Combine remaining margarine and cocoa in saucepan. Add 1/3 cup buttermilk.
Bring to a boil.
Blend in confectioners sugar and remaining vanilla.
Pour over warm brownies.

title: cinnamon bundt cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease Bundt pan.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together in a small bowl.
Cut biscuits into fourths.
Place nuts in bottom of Bundt pan.
Dip 2 cans biscuits in sugar/cinnamon mixture and place in Bundt pan.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Spread cabbage on bottom of 3-quart greased casserole.
Brown beef and onion in a little oil.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Add rice, spread over cabbage.
Pour soup, tomatoes and water over beef, rice and cabbage.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: low calorie vegetable soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook until carrots are tender, about 1 hour.

title: christmas tree salad
directions: Dissolve raspberry
jello
in
1 1/4 cups of hot water; chill until
syrupy.
Combine
ground
cranberries,
crushed pineapple, diced marshmallows and sugar;
mix and chill.
Whip cream; fold into chilled fruit mixture.
Fold in jello.
Mold and chill. Serves 12.

title: skillet chicken with mac and cheese
directions: Spray large skillet with nonstick cooking spray. Add chicken; cook and stir on medium-high heat 5 to 6 minutes, until chicken is cooked through. Add 1 1/2 cups water, milk and macaroni. Bring to a boil; reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 15 minutes, until macaroni is tender, stirring once or twice. Add contents of cheese pouch, stir until well blended.

title: mini sausage pizzas
directions: Open English muffins.
Spread on cookie sheets.
Spoon 1 tablespoon sauce on each muffin.
Fry pork sausage; strain off fat.
Sprinkle cooked, drained sausage on each muffin.
Again, spoon 1 tablespoon sauce on top of sausage.
Cover with grated cheeses.
Bake in 425° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Mix eggs, oil and sugar.
Add dry ingredients.
Add zucchini and vanilla. Add nuts.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake 50 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix, butter, water, oil and 1/2 can of Eagle Brand milk.
Pour 1/2 of batter in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Melt caramels and remaining Eagle Brand milk.
Pour over baked cake.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Pour remaining batter over baked cake.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: bran muffins by the pailful
directions: Combine brans and salt. Stir in boiling water, then buttermilk. Cool to lukewarm.
In mixing bowl, cream together sugar and shortening. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir into bran mixture.
Combine flour and baking soda. Add to bran mixture and stir just enough to dampen dry ingredients. Store batter in refrigerator until ready to use.
(It will keep 4 weeks.) When ready to use, preheat oven to 375°.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake in preheated oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Makes about 72 medium muffins.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: In a 9 x 9-inch baking dish, layer the beans, pepper, onions and tomatoes.
Fry hamburger, adding chili powder until brown. Layer on top of tomatoes.
Mix corn meal batter and pour on top of hamburger.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: oven bake french toast
directions: Arrange bread slices in a single layer, with sides touching, in a greased jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle raisins and pecans over bread.
In a medium bowl, whisk eggs, half and half, liqueur, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg.
Pour egg mixture over bread.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the margarine.
Add the sugar.
Cream well. Blend bananas, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, soda and salt. Add sour milk.
May add 1/2 cup chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: just cookies
directions: Bring to a boil for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes the oleo, sugar, milk and cocoa.
Add peanut butter, oatmeal, (2 optional ingredients) and vanilla. Stir. Drop on wax paper by teaspoon.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into crust.
Let stand in the refrigerator.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Beat until smooth.
Fill papers 1/3 full.
Top with heaping tablespoonful of cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Pour in baked pie shell.
Makes 3 pies.

title: no cholesterol cocoa squares
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jellyroll pan.
In a large saucepan, combine water, cocoa and oleo.
Cook over medium heat, stirring often, until mixture comes to a full boil.
Remove from heat; stir in flour and sugar.
Add egg substitute, yogurt, baking soda and salt; mix thoroughly with spoon.
Pour batter into the prepared pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Sprinkle powdered sugar over top.
Cut into squares.
Makes 32 servings.

title: cabbage and ground beef
directions: Cut up green cabbage leaves, red bell pepper and green bell pepper and place in saucepan. Add ground beef, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper to vegetables mixture and stir at times while cooking on medium heat until done. Next, cut up the head of cabbage and place in pot. Stir in the ground beef sauce mixture; cover with lid and cook on medium heat, stirring continuously until cabbage is done.

title: hot relish
directions: Simmer for 2 to 3 hours until desired thickness is obtained. Pour into hot jars and seal.
(Be warned that this is hot and spicy; 1 cup of chopped hot peppers can be used to "mild" it down.)

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef with onion, then add Ragu sauce and simmer. Mix in medium bowl 12 ounces cottage cheese, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, 2 eggs, 2 tablespoons parsley and 1 teaspoon pepper.
Set aside.
Layer small amount meat mixture, dry noodles, cottage cheese mixture and Mozzarella cheese, starting and ending with meat sauce.
Pour 1 cup water over all and bake.
Can be assembled day ahead and refrigerated.
Allow an extra 15 minutes baking time.

title: cheese straws
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Prepare pie crust for a 9-inch two crust pie as directed on package except stir in cheese with hot water. Roll each round into 13 x 10-inch rectangle.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
With sharp knife, cut each rectangle lengthwise into 3 strips, then crosswise into 30 strips.
Do not separate strips.
Sprinkle with caraway seed and paprika.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot.
Makes about 15 dozen straws.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 1 can tomato sauce.
Mix well. Place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Pour second can of tomato sauce on top of meat loaf and bake 15 minutes longer. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.
Best after 1 day old.
Can use fresh tomatoes.

title: cherry crumb cake
directions: Mix everything together except pie filling.
Reserve 1 cup of the crumb mixture for topping.
Pat into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole dish that has been sprayed with a nonfat cooking spray. Pour can of pie filling on top of crumb mixture.
Sprinkle the rest of crumb mixture (1 cup) on top of pie filling.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour in a slow oven (300°).
Serve warm with vanilla nonfat yogurt or Dream Whip.
Sprinkle Grape-Nuts cereal on top if desired.
Fat: 0.37 g. Yields 8 to 12 servings.

title: cowboy soup
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 40 minutes.
Good served with cornbread.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and vanilla thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour, sifted with baking powder and soda, alternately with sour cream.
In another bowl, cream margarine, brown sugar and cinnamon together.
Add nuts and mix well.
Fold brown sugar mixture into the batter.
Pour into greased tube pan and bake at 350° about 50 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes; then remove from pan at once.

title: 9 day slaw
directions: Pour 2 cups sugar over cabbage, 1 onion and 1 bell pepper. Bring oil, vinegar, salt, sugar and celery seed to a boil.
Let cool and pour over cabbage mixture.
Chill 24 hours.

title: play dough
directions: Mix flour, salt and cream of tartar in a saucepan. Add water, oil and food coloring.
Cook, stirring, for 3 minutes or until mixture pulls away from pan.
Knead immediately.
Store in airtight container.
Kids love to make this and will play for hours.

title: fresh veggie salad
directions: Mix in small bottle of low-fat Italian dressing. Marinate overnight. Next day, stir again and drain.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Beat butter until creamy.
Beat in sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in vanilla.
Stir in flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Set aside 1/4 cup flour mixture.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream.
Stir in mashed bananas and nuts with reserved flour to add to mixture and blend. Put in a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Melt margarine.
Roll chicken in margarine, then roll in cracker mixture.
Place in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: chile and cheese dip
directions: Mix both ingredients together.
Heat in microwave until blended.
Serve hot with chips.

title: greek egg lemon soup(avgolemono)
directions: Bring chicken broth to a boil; salt to taste.
Add rice and simmer uncovered for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat.
In bowl, beat egg whites until stiff; add yolks and beat well.
Slowly add lemon juice to eggs, beating constantly.
Add 2 cups of hot broth, slowly.
Do not stop beating, constant beating will prevent curdling.
When eggs and broth are well mixed, pour mixture back into remaining broth and rice.
Stir well over heat.
Do not let boil.
Serve immediately in warm bowls with thinly sliced lemons and parsley for garnish.

title: maple syrup
directions: Stir sugar, brown sugar, cream of tartar and water until full boil; turn to low.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add vanilla and maple flavor.

title: pumpernickel caper dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Taste improves after left refrigerated overnight.
Best to make ahead.
Serve with pumpernickel bread sliced into bite-size pieces.
Also, good with fresh vegetables. Can be served in a hollowed out round loaf of pumpernickel bread for a special occasion.

title: taco dip
directions: Whip together the sour cream and cream cheese.
Add taco seasoning; mix together.
Put in dish and chill for at least 1 hour.
Cover mixture with taco sauce (mild, medium or hot).
Put on top shredded lettuce, cheese, cubed tomatoes, olives, etc. (whatever you want).
Ready to serve with tortilla chips.

title: delicious drink(instant cocoa)
directions: Mix together.
Use 1/3 cup of mixture to 1 cup of hot water.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Peel and slice zucchini; take out seeds.
Boil until tender; drain and put in unbaked pie shell.
Mix together the remaining ingredients and pour over zucchini in pie shell. Dot with butter. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: harvest cake
directions: Blend dry ingredients.
Drain sweet potatoes and beat with mixer.
Add liquid and dry ingredients to sweet potato puree and blend well.
Add nuts or raisins.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Ice with cream cheese icing or other white icing.

title: hot party crab dip
directions: Blend all ingredients but almonds.
Put in baking dish. Sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: tomato fritters
directions: Stir just until mixed.
Drop by tablespoon into hot oil.
Cook until brown on each side.
May be served as a vegetable with meats or with cocktails as hors d'oeuvres.

title: special k loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients in the order given.
Let stand about 15 minutes before baking to be sure the cereal absorbs all the moisture.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes to an hour or until nice and brown.
Can be done the day before, and only bake about 30 minutes, so won't dry out or get too brown.
May cover with foil at the end of baking.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Grease 2-quart round casserole dish.
In large bowl with fork, mix flour and next 4 ingredients.
Cut in butter until it resembles crumbs.
Stir in raisins and caraway seed.
Beat egg slightly. Reserve 1 tablespoon of egg.
Stir in remaining eggs and buttermilk into flour mixture until slightly sticky.

title: cooked chocolate frosting
directions: Melt margarine in heavy saucepan or iron skillet.
Add other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Cook 2 or 3 minutes.
Cool and spread on layer cake.

title: meat loaf with vegetables
directions: Combine meat, salt, egg, 1/2 can of tomato sauce, seasoning and 3/4 cup onion rings.
Form loaves.
Place potatoes around loaves.
Cover and bake at 375° for 35 minutes, then place vegetables around meat.
Stir and combine with potatoes.
Top meat with rest of tomato sauce.
Bake for 20 minutes, uncovered.
Add remaining onion rings the last 10 minutes, uncovered.

title: chicken almond hash
directions: Melt butter; add flour.
Blend and cook until bubbly.
Add milk slowly and stirring constantly.
Simmer until thickened.
Add the chicken, mushrooms and almonds.
Spoon mixture over warmed English muffins; top with grated Swiss cheese.
Put under broiler to melt cheese.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Mash bananas.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl and mix well. Transfer to prepared pan.
Bake until top is golden brown and splits slightly, about 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Do not double recipe.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Mix ingredients and chicken breasts.
Cook in microwave 12 minutes.
Take out and turn chicken breasts over.
Cook another 15 minutes, then you're done.

title: delicious old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add shortening, mixing with fork.
Add eggs and flavoring.
Roll out thin on floured surface. Cut with floured cookie cutters.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen large cookies.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: In a large bowl combine soup, milk, salt, pepper, onion and pimento.
Add
potatoes;
mix
well.
Pour
into
a
well greased 2
quart
casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 370° for 1 or 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are tender.

title: aunt opal's lasagna
directions: Day before or early in day:
In hot oil in skillet, saute onion.
Add beef and cook until red color disappears.
Slice garlic.
Mash with salt.
Add to meat with pepper, oregano, parsley, tomatoes, tomato sauce and 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese. Simmer covered for 30 minutes.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: lemon pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together. Pour into graham cracker crust and refrigerate until firm.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Combine crust mixture and form in bottom of cake pan.
Save 1 cup of this cake mix for the topping.

title: pineapple cheese pie
directions: Cook until thick and clear the sugar, cornstarch and pineapple. Cool.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, salt and eggs.
Add milk and vanilla.
Pour pineapple mixture on bottom of pie shell.
Then add cream cheese mixture.
You can sprinkle 1/4 chopped pecans on top if desired.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes and then at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes until done.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Beat egg white and water until foamy; stir in nuts, coating well.
Combine sugar and remaining ingredients; sprinkle over nuts and stir until evenly coated.
Spread the nuts in a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Cool and store in airtight container.

title: aunt julie's corn casserole
directions: Mix the first 10 ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Mix melted butter and cracker crumbs.
Pour cracker mixture on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until golden.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: forever amber
directions: Mix together orange slices, coconut, pecans and Eagle Brand milk.
Place in cooker and bake at 300° for 25 minutes.
Cool. Roll in balls, then roll balls in powdered sugar or coconut.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or Pyrex dish, put rice, oleo, water and
soups.
Lay
chicken on top of this and bake uncovered for
1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Check to see if more water is needed as rice cooks.

title: chocolate swirled peanut butter squares
directions: In bowl, stir together flour and brown sugar.
Using pastry blender, cut in margarine and 1/2 cup peanut butter until coarse crumbs form.
Press crumb mixture onto the bottom of a 10 x 15 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown; cool.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli very fine.
Use all the tops and only part of the stalks.
(Chop stalks in Cuisinart.)
Mix all ingredients together.

title: black bottom cups
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; beat well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Set aside.
Mix flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt.
Add remaining ingredients to the flour mixture and beat well.
Fill muffin cups 1/3 full with chocolate batter; top with heaping teaspoonfuls of cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar and chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 18 cupcakes.

title: grape hull pie
directions: Wash grapes.
Pop with fingers, separating pulp and skin into two bowls.
Place skins in pot.
Cover with water; boil until tender.
Boil pulp about 5 minutes.
Pour in strainer; mash with spoon to get seeds out when skin is tender.
Add pulp, cornstarch, salt, cinnamon, sugar and butter.
Cook until thick.
Pour in number 2 pie shells.
Cover with top crust.
Bake at 400° until crust is brown.
Makes 2 pies.

title: tzatziki
directions: In a large bowl mix all the ingredients, first the yogurt, the cucumber, then the garlic and the olive oil.
Cover the bowl and keep refrigerated.
When you're about to serve, sprinkle with dill.

title: moon cakes
directions: Cream butter well; add sugar gradually.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Add flour and baking powder a little at a time and blend well with lemon juice.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in well-greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Cool completely.
Cut with water glass into moon shapes.

title: easy peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar and syrup together until spins a thread.
Add raw peanuts; cook until brown.
Remove from heat; add soda and salt. Pour on buttered pizza pan.

title: copper pennies
directions: Mix soup, oil, vinegar, sugar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour mixture over carrots, pepper and onion.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Keeps for several days.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Combine lemonade, Cool Whip and condensed milk. Mix well. Pour into baked or graham cracker pie shell. Chill.

title: grandma hazel's barbecued beans
directions: Brown ground round; add chopped onion and remaining ingredients.
Start with a little sugar, mustard, liquid smoke and ketchup; measure according to taste.
Simmer in pot to cook on top of stove.

title: pepper fillets
directions: Dry the steaks.

Press pepper into steaks with heel of hand. Let stand 30 minutes. Meanwhile, mix butter, tabasco sauce, worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, cognac and chopped parsley. Put a light layer of salt over heavy skillet on HIGH heat.
When the salt yellows, add the steak.
Lower the heat to moderate. Cook to desired doneness.
Heat the butter, worcestershire sauce, and tabasco on low; add cognac and flame.

title: cheese cake
directions: Use a spring-pan; spread inside of pan with butter; set oven at 375°. Mix all of the crust ingredients together and spread in bottom of pan, pushing crumbs toward sides of pan to cover seam between sides of pan and bottom.

title: ham balls
directions: Lightly grease 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place about 2 inches apart in pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until brown. Serve warm.
Yield: about 7 dozen.
Bake at 350°.

title: maple-coconut rice pudding
directions: Coat a 2-quart baking dish with nonstick spray, and add the rice and coconut.
In medium bowl, whisk the milk, maple syrup, cinnamon and eggs; pour over the rice.
Stir to combine.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° until set, about 45 to 50 minutes.

title: fried turkey breast
directions: Cut turkey into strips.
Soak in milk.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Flour.
Deep fry in grease until golden brown.

title: no bake chocolate squares
directions: Cook
until boiling sugar and syrup.
Remove from heat, stir in	peanut butter.	Add Rice Krispies.
Spread evenly in buttered 9
x
13-inch
pan.
Melt
morsels in double boiler. Spread over the mixture.
Cut in 1-inch squares before it gets hard.

title: mandarin chicken breasts
directions: On stove top over low heat, brown chicken breasts in nonstick skillet. Combine onion soup mix, pineapple chunks and mandarin oranges. Pour over chicken breasts. Simmer for 30 to 40 minutes or until chicken is done. Makes 4 servings.

title: stromboli
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Thaw bread and let it rise.
Press dough onto greased cookie sheet into a rectangular shape.
Mix the mayonnaise and mustard together.
Spread mixture over pressed out dough.
Spread meat and cheeses evenly over dough.
Wrap dough (one side over the other) so that meat and cheese are covered.
Sprinkle top of loaf with garlic salt and pepper.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix 1/2 of the margarine with all other ingredients. Top with rest of margarine and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter icing or candy
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and milk in a 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for one minute.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat well.
Spread on cake.

title: blueberry nut crunch
directions: Lightly
grease
a
x
13-inch
baking dish.
Spread undrained crushed pineapple over bottom of pan.
Add the layer of blueberries
and the sugar.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top. Drizzle melted butter on top.
Top with pecans.

title: easy butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Mixture will be stiff.
Drop in small mounds on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° until lightly brown.

title: punch
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Make 1 gallon- finish filling with water.
Freeze.
Then, 4 hours before serving, take from freezer and add 1/2 liter ginger ale and 1/2 gallon pineapple sherbet.

title: grilled turkey breast with orange and rosemary
directions: Chop shallots finely.
Place in large Ziploc bag.
Add next 8 ingredients.
Seal and shake.
Place turkey breast between 2 sheets plastic, flatten to 1-inch thick.
Place in bag and leave 12 hours. Remove meat and barbecue or broil to 155°.
Brush occasionally with marinade, 12 minutes per side.
Serve with wild rice and summer squash.

title: dalma's chicken
directions: Roll the chicken breasts in grated Parmesan cheese.
Mix the remainder of the ingredients together, including the liquid from the mushrooms.
Lightly cover the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan with some of the sauce.
Arrange the chicken pieces in the pan and cover with the remainder of the sauce.
Top with any Parmesan cheese that remains from coating the chicken and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for approximately 1 1/2 hours, until done.

title: savory pot roast
directions: In a 6-quart Dutch oven, in hot oil, cook roast until browned on all sides.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in mushroom soup, onion soup mix and 1 cup of the water.
Reduce to low.
Cover; simmer for 2 hours, or until meat is tender, turning occasionally.
Add vegetables.
Cover; cook for 40 minutes, or until roast and vegetables are tender.
Remove roast and vegetables to platter.

title: watergate cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine cake and pudding mix.
Add other ingredients.
Beat four minutes.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 45 minutes to one hour.
Cool and ice.

title: the biscuit
directions: In a 2-quart mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except biscuit mix.
Use a wire whisk and mix until there is a smooth consistency.
Add biscuit mix, changing to a large spoon to work biscuit mix into tonic water mixture.
Dip kneading hand into just enough additional biscuit mix that dough can be kneaded in the bowl until smooth and elastic.
Knead about 12 times in bowl. Divide the dough into 14 equal pieces and shape into biscuits, about 1 1/2-inches thick.

title: buttermilk fried fish
directions: Thaw fish if frozen. Cut fish into serving-sized portions and place in a shallow dish. Pour buttermilk over fish; cover and refrigerate for 30 minutes, turning once. In a large bowl, combine biscuit mix and salt; remove fish from buttermilk and coat with biscuit mix mixture. In a large skillet, heat oil; place fish in skillet in single layer and cook until it is browned on both sides and flakes easily with a fork. Drain fish on paper towels and serve.

title: spoon bread
directions: Position rack in center of a 425° oven.
Pour oil into a 2-quart souffle dish.
Put dish in oven while preparing batter. Bring water and salt to a boil in a heavy large saucepan over medium heat.
Gradually whisk in cornmeal and cook until thick, stirring constantly about 2 minutes.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix flour, eggs and sugar with pineapple.
Place in buttered casserole.
Cover with bread cubes.
Pour melted butter over all. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Delicious with baked ham.

title: apricot bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except jam, together.
Press 2/3 of mixture in an ungreased 8 x 8-inch pan. Cover with apricot jam.
Cover with remaining mixture.
Bake for 35 minutes.

title: watercress soup
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water for 25 minutes.
Drain and put aside.
Peel leaves off of the watercress.
Cook in a pan of 2 cups of water for 8 to 10 minutes on medium to low heat.
Drain well.

title: chicken corn saute(low fat, low calorie)
directions: Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Combine chili powder and salt in a shallow dish.
Add chicken and turn to coat.
Heat 1 tablespoon of oil in a large skillet on medium high heat.
Add chicken, cook until no longer pink in center.
Remove to serving dish.
Heat remaining oil in skillet.
Add onion.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes or until tender.
Add bell peppers, cook and stir 3 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Add corn, heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Return chicken to skillet to reheat.

title: lime refresher
directions: In a saucepan, cook 3 cups of water with sugar over moderate heat, stirring, until sugar is dissolved.
Remove pan from heat and cool syrup.
In a large pitcher, stir together syrup, remaining 7 cups water, lime juice and lime slices and garnish with mint.

title: king ranch hamburger
directions: Brown hamburger meat, drain well.
Add onion, garlic and mushrooms.
Saute until tender.
Add soups, milk, Ro-Tel and chili powder.
Put 1/4 to 1/3 cup mixture in 9 x 11-inch baking pan and spread thinly.

title: potato-chip chicken
directions: Chop or crush the potato chips.
Melt the butter in a saucepan and pour melted butter into a shallow bowl.
Put the chips in another bowl and season them with black pepper.
Dip each chicken breast into the melted butter and then into the chips, covering the chicken completely with chips.
After all breasts have been coated, place them in a shallow baking dish (or on a baking sheet) sprayed with cooking spray.
If you have any chips leftover, pour them over the breasts and press down to secure them to the chicken.

title: whole wheat oatmeal cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Stir together whole wheat flour, baking soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oats, walnuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheets for 1 or 2 minutes before removing to wire racks to cool.

title: skillet spanish rice
directions: Heat oil in large skillet; add rice and brown slightly.
Add onions, peppers and beef.
Stir over high heat until meat is lightly browned.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and bring quickly to boil.
Cover tightly and simmer 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: turnip relish
directions: Grind all vegetables through a food chopper.
Add salt and mix well.
Let stand one hour.
Mix together sugar, mustard seed and vinegar (also celery seed if you use it).
Heat just to boiling point and sugar is melted; cool.
Drain salted vegetables thoroughly; combine with cooled vinegar mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Let stand for one hour.
Pack in sterile jars and seal, but do not cook.
Store in cool place.

title: hershey pie
directions: *You can use plain chocolate bars.

title: tipsy sweet potatoes
directions: Put in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: collard soup
directions: Taste fruit for salt because all canned has salt.
Pepper to taste and add a few dashes of hot sauce.
Use 5 or 6 chorizo (Spanish sausage).
If sausage is not available, use pepperoni. Start with tomatoes, ham hocks, onions, sausage, garlic and beans. Cook about 30 minutes.
Add all other ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Decrease heat and simmer 3 hours.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: Blend flour, shortening and salt with pastry blender or fork until pieces are the size of peas.
Mix vinegar, egg and water separately.
Moisten dry ingredients gradually, mixing lightly. Let dough stand in refrigerator for several minutes, then roll out.
Unused dough can be frozen.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Stir in oats and peanut butter.
Drop cookies on wax paper.
Let cool. Eat and enjoy.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Stir together the margarine, sugar and milk.
Bring to full boil for 5 minutes over medium heat, or until 234° on candy thermometer.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips; stir until melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares.
Makes about 3 pounds.

title: green bean casserole
directions: (If frozen, use 1/2 cup salted water to cook beans until tender, then drain.)
Butter a casserole, make two layers--first beans, then soup, then cheese, then beans, soup and cheese. Scatter sliced almonds over cheese topping.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 6.

title: spaghetti amore
directions: Add mushroom soup, tomato soup, water and garlic.
Heat and blend in 1/2 cup shredded mild Cheddar cheese.
Add soup mixture to spaghetti, cooked and drained, into 9 x 13-inch pan along with hamburger mixture.
Top with 1/2 cup shredded mild Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes (no lid).

title: copper pennies
directions: Slice and cook carrots until tender; drain.
Set aside.
Add onion, pepper and celery to carrots.
Boil together soup, sugar, vinegar, oil and mustard.
Pour over carrots.
Will keep several weeks in refrigerator.

title: cereal peanut bars
directions: Combine corn syrup, brown sugar and salt in a saucepan.
Bring to a full boil. Stir in peanut butter.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla, crisp rice cereal, crushed corn flakes and chocolate pieces.
Press into buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill one hour. Cut into bars and store in refrigerator.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: cheese soup
directions: Boil bouillon cubes, water, celery, carrots, potatoes and onions for 20 minutes.
Add frozen vegetables and cook until tender.
Add cream of chicken soup, 1/2 can of water and cheese. Stir until desired consistency.
Serves 8.

title: orange whole wheat pancakes
directions: Beat eggs and oil together.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to eggs.
Gradually add orange juice until batter is consistency desired.
Fry pancakes on medium hot griddle and serve immediately.
Top with yogurt or peanut butter.
For variation, add chopped nuts to the batter.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute the onion in the margarine.
Cook the broccoli.
Mix the broccoli with the onion, rice, chicken soup and Cheez Whiz.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered casserole dish and cover.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fish fillet casserole
directions: Butter a Pyrex dish.
Place fish side by side and spread soup evenly over the top.
Sprinkle cheese over it, pepper and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Fillet of haddock or halibut can be used if you wish.
Serves 4.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Yield: 3 dozen.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients and place in buttered casserole.
Top with crushed corn flakes and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients in large Dutch oven (or chicken can be floured and browned first).
Cook on top of stove (or in 325° oven) for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with tossed salad and toasted French bread.

title: bird's nest
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels in pan large enough to add other 2 ingredients.
Mix in peanuts and noodles.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper and cool.
(You may want to refrigerate for one hour or so.)

title: aunt emma's pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers; cover cucumbers with water.
Stir in lime. Cover; let set 24 hours.
Wash every 1/2 hour for 4 hours.
Bring to boil vinegar, sugar and pickling spices tied in cloth.
Pour over cucumbers; let set overnight.
Heat to a boil.
Add 1 tablespoon turmeric.
Put in jars and seal.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Use large leaf of lettuce to line bowl.
Tear lettuce into bite size pieces.
Put carrots (drained) on top of lettuce.
Put onion rings on top of carrots.
Put green peas over onion rings.
Put green pepper over peas and sprinkle cheese to cover.
Mix sugar and mayonnaise (will not cover completely).
Sprinkle top with Bac*Os. Refrigerate 12 hours.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs, margarine, sugar, baking powder, flour and salt. Add milk, 1 teaspoon vanilla and corn.
Bake at 350° for about 55 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat; add taco seasoning according to package directions.
Set aside to cool.
Combine all ingredients, except tortilla chips; mix well.
Sprinkle chips on top just before serving.

title: corn chile bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a well buttered 2-quart souffle dish.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: baked rice and beans with monterey jack
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
In a large, nonstick skillet over medium-high heat, warm the oil until hot but not smoking.
Add the onion and garlic; saute until softened, 3 to 5 minutes.
Add the bell pepper and jalapeno pepper; saute until the bell pepper is softened, about 3 minutes.
Stir in the tomatoes, lime juice, chili powder, oregano and salt; bring to a simmer.
In a 2-quart casserole, stir together the beans, rice and 1/2 of the scallions. Pour in the tomato mixture; stir to combine.
