Sprinkle the casserole with the cheese; bake for 10 to 15 minutes, or until the rice and beans are heated through and the cheese is bubbly. Sprinkle with the remaining scallions and serve.
Serves 4.

title: orange poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients except poppy seed in a small glass bowl.
Stir well.
Microwave at High 1/2 to 2 minutes or until slightly thickened, stirring after 1 minute.
Let mixture cool, stir in poppy seed.
Cover and chill.
Makes 3/4 cup.
Use on spinach/strawberry or orange mandarin/almond and lettuce leaf salad.
Also good on fresh fruit.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown ground beef in a skillet; drain fat.
Add barbecue sauce; stir and simmer on low heat.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Place biscuits in a pie pan; spread out into a crust.
Add ground beef mixture.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Place pan in oven; bake until biscuits rise and brown.

title: fruit punch bars
directions: Grease and flour bottom of a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan. Beat eggs and sugar in a large mixer bowl at high speed until light and fluffy.
Add fruit cocktail, flour, soda, salt and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed until well blended; spread in pan. Sprinkle with coconut and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
While hot, drizzle with glaze. Cool and cut into bars.

title: hot taco dip
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add onions, catsup and beans. Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes or until thick.
Put in glass baking dish.
Top with cheese and olives.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Serve hot with corn chips.

title: duck salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: toffee butter crunch(great christmas candy)
directions: Butter sides of heavy 2-quart saucepan.
In it melt butter; add sugar, water and corn syrup.
Cook over medium heat to 290° (soft crack), stirring frequently, after it reaches 280°.
Remove from heat.
Add nuts.
Immediately pour onto 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Wait 2 to 3 minutes until toffee is firmer to add the chocolate. Sprinkle the pieces on top and spread around.
Sprinkle with finely chopped nuts.
Chill until chocolate is firm.
Break into pieces.
Yields 1 1/2 pounds.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix by hand all except brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour half in pan.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon together. Sprinkle on top.
Pour in the rest of the batter. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
While cake
is hot, mix powdered sugar, milk and vanilla together.
Pour over cake.
Cool before cutting.

title: death by chocolate
directions: In a 9 x 13 inch pan, bake cake according to package directions.
Cool and crumble.
Make pudding according to package directions with milk.
In a large trifle or other glass serving bowl, place half the crumbled cake.
Pour half of the coffee over the cake and spread half of the pudding over that. Top with half of the whipped topping, sprinkled with half the crumbled candy bars.
Repeat layers in the same order.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: peanut butter blossoms(makes 3 dozen)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients together with hands. Shape into balls and roll into sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes, then 2 minutes after placing Hershey's Kisses in center of cookies.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Serves a very large group.

title: spanish casserole
directions: Brown beef, then add next 4 ingredients.
Let simmer over low heat; grate cheese.
Put a layer of chips in a baking dish. Add casserole mixture, then cheese.
Continue this procedure and end with casserole mixture and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: butterscotch sauce
directions: Melt together first 3 ingredients.
Stir in vinegar and cinnamon.
Serve on sliced apples.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef with chopped onion and green pepper, garlic and pepper.
Drain grease.
Add tomato sauce, paste and Ro-Tel.
Add sugar, then spices.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
In separate bowl, combine Ricotta with eggs and Parmesan.
Cook noodles with a little oil.

title: milly's baked supreme carrots
directions: Shred carrots to make 3 cups.
Add salt to taste and cook in smallest amount of water possible for 5 to 7 minutes.
While carrots are cooking, melt 2 tablespoons butter; add 2 tablespoons flour, 1 cup milk and 3/4 cup grated cheese.
Put carrots in casserole with 1/4 cup green pepper and 1/4 cup chopped onion. Pour sauce over vegetables and top with buttered crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: holiday pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, pour into three greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
(Do not overbake)
Frost with following.

title: roast corn-on-the-cob
directions: Remove husk and silk from corn.
Place each ear of corn on a piece of aluminum foil.
Add 1 tablespoon butter and 1 ice cube. Wrap securely, twisting ends to make handles for turning.
Place corn on grill.
Cook for 25 minutes, turning once.
Season with salt, pepper and additional butter, if desired.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Blend all ingredients and chill.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix sausage, beef, bread crumbs, minced onion, egg and milk together.
Roll into 1-inch diameter balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Drain off grease.

title: turnip casserole
directions: Salt and cook enough turnips for 6 cups.
Drain and mash.
Add softened cream cheese, sugar and margarine; mix well.
Pour into casserole and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, hot and lightly browned.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
Rutabagas or carrots may be used also.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and eggs.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add remainder of ingredients and beat until well blended.
Turn into well-greased loaf pan and bake at 350° to 375° for one hour.

title: carrot cake
directions: Stir together the first 7 ingredients; then add the next 7 ingredients.
Fold in egg whites last.
Cook in a tube pan at about 300° until done.

title: mother's stuffing(for 18-pound turkey)
directions: Cube the bread.
In a large skillet, place 1 1/2 cups oleo and the onion.
Cook over low heat until onion is brown.
Add 6 cups bread cubes; toss until oleo soaks into bread.
Put rest of cubes in bowl; toss with buttered cubes.
Add the celery, salt, pepper and poultry seasoning; toss again.
Add hot water to moisten, if desired.
Stuff in turkey cavity; bake according to turkey directions, or bake in pan at 450° for about 30 minutes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers, onions and bell peppers.
Pack in gallon jug starting with layer of cucumbers, then onions and peppers until jug is full.
Pack down as it will shrink some.

title: divinity candy
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water; stir until dissolved. Cook until it forms a hard-ball in cold water.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together first 8 ingredients.
Add nuts, then oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Then add pumpkin and pour into 3 well-greased 1 pound coffee cans, filling each one half full.
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 250°.
Cool 15 minutes in cans, then remove to wire rack.
(I use 5 cans about the size of a 10 ounce peanut can.)

title: one pan chicken
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli or asparagus.
Arrange crosswise in a buttered or sprayed 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan.
Mix Bisquick, milk, egg and soup.
Beat with a wire whisk.
Pour over broccoli in center of dish.
Fry chicken cutlets in peanut oil until brown. Cut into bite size pieces.
Add to dish.
Mix in.
Add pimentos. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peach and cottage cheese salad(single serving)
directions: Combine cottage cheese, cinnamon and sweetener; mix well.
Add rice and peach.
Toss lightly until well mixed, chill.
Just before serving, pour skim milk over mixture.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Mix first three ingredients and pour over chicken pieces. Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: italian pizza pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large skillet, brown meat.
Drain meat and return to skillet.
Add onions.
Cook until onions are tender.
Add garlic powder, tomato sauce and Italian seasoning. Simmer 10 minutes.
Pour into pie shell and top with shredded cheese.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.

title: one dish chicken and rice bake
directions: In a 2-quart shallow baking dish, mix soup, water, rice, paprika and pepper. Mix in vegetables. Cut up chicken breast in mix or leave whole on top. Sprinkle with additional paprika and pepper. Cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until chicken and rice are done.

title: cranberry mustard
directions: Blend in double boiler until thick.
Store in jar in refrigerator.
Serve with pretzels.

title: veggie bites(appetizers)
directions: Press crescent rolls in 9 x 13-inch pan (ungreased) and up the sides; prick the bottom with fork.
Mix beaten eggs with soup mix packet, broccoli and cottage cheese.
Pour over unbaked crust. Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or until center is set.
Cool 10 minutes before cutting into bite-size pieces.

title: cream cheese spread
directions: Combine cream cheese and salad dressing until well blended. Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
May be formed to different shapes and decorated with pimientos and parsley.
Serve with crackers.

title: hot milk sponge cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and beat well.
Sift together flour and baking powder and add gradually.
Scald milk and add gradually. Add vanilla.
Bake in ungreased tube pan in 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until done.
Turn upside down to cool.
This cake is good with fresh strawberries or a chocolate glaze.

title: singapore satay
directions: Cut pieces of meat 3/4-inch square and 1/2-inch thick.
Blend shallots, garlic, lemon grass and ginger together.
Mix in spices, salt, turmeric and brown sugar.
Soak tamarind in 1/4 cup warm water 5 minutes.
Squeeze and strain for juice.
Add to other ingredients.
Mix well; stir in meat.
Marinate for at least 6 hours.
If possible, use bamboo skewers soaked in cold water 1 hour.
Thread 4 to 5 pieces of meat onto each skewer and cook over charcoals or under broiler until golden brown.
Baste frequently with oil while cooking.
Serve with sauce.

title: onion potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In glass pie plate or microwave-safe shallow dish, combine potatoes and water.
Cover with wax paper and then microwave on High 10 minutes, stirring once halfway through cooking.
Meanwhile, in 8 or 9-inch nonstick skillet, heat 2 teaspoons olive oil over medium-high heat.
Add garlic and cook 30 seconds.
Add onions and peppers; cook, covered, 10 minutes stirring occasionally.

title: autumn apple delight
directions: Peel and slice 2 large apples and place in 7-Up to soak (stops the browning).
Use 12 or 16 ounce roll of cookie dough and spread on lightly greased pizza pan.
Bake.
Cool cookie dough and spread mixture of cream cheese, brown sugar, vanilla and milk on top of dough.
Drain apples and arrange on top of cream cheese.
Drizzle with ice cream topping.
Top with peanuts.

title: oriental stir-fry
directions: Heat 12 inch nonstick skillet.
Add oil and heat.
Add chicken, garlic and ginger; sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika and cook, stirring quickly and frequently, until chicken is no longer pink, 1 to 2 minutes.
Add vegetables and half the broth and stir to combine.
Cover and let cook until vegetables are tender-crisp, 1 to 2 minutes.

title: margaritas
directions: Mix juice, ice, liqueur and tequila.
Can be frozen.
Before serving, if you like, dip the rim of glass in water and then in salt.
Makes 2 servings.

title: cranberry mousse
directions: In medium saucepan over medium heat, bring juice to a boil; remove from heat.
Stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Beat cranberry sauce until almost smooth.
Mix juice and gelatin together.
Put in refrigerator until slightly thickened, then fold in whipped cream.
This mixture can be:

title: thai salty egg(side dish)
directions: Add salt to water and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat. Cool to lukewarm.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: In large skillet, mix together.
Add meatballs.
Cook 1 hour (simmer).
Drip off excess grease.
Can also be frozen.

title: irish bread
directions: Mix in each ingredient as you add them.
Grease and flour (or use Baker's Joy) a large black cast-iron frying pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour, or until done.

title: white pizza dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

In shallow 1-quart casserole, combine savory herb with garlic soup mix, sour cream, Ricotta cheese, 3/4 cup shredded Mozzarella, mushrooms and pepperoni. Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup cheese. Bake 30 minutes or until heated through. Serve with bread.

title: fruited creme salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add ice cream and stir until melted. Add cherries, pineapple and nuts.
Place in 2-quart mold and refrigerate.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: cherry pound cake
directions: Heat raisins and water until boiling.
Take off heat and add margarine.
Cool until lukewarm.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° about 20 minutes or until done.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: In a large bowl, sift together flour, cinnamon, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Set aside.
In another large bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, then oil, mixing well after each addition.
Beat in vanilla.

title: pimiento cheese
directions: Grate the Cheddar cheese and add the softened cream cheese. Add the other ingredients.
Add enough mayonnaise so it will be spreadable.
I find that it works better to mix with your hands.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Thoroughly mix shortening, sugar and eggs. Stir in milk and vanilla.
Blend well. Sift in flour, soda and salt.
Stir in nuts and chips. Chill 1 hour. Drop by rounded spoonful 2-inches apart on greased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Yields 4 dozen.

title: pistachio heart cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well. Stir together flour and cornstarch; gradually add to creamed mixture.
Wrap dough and chill at least 1 hour.

title: beef-barley soup(dieter's recipe)
directions: Preparation Time: 23 minutes.
Cooking Time: 1 1/4 hours.

title: cheesy vegetable enchiladas
directions: Cook in oil peppers, carrot, half of onions, chili powder, garlic, until tender.
Add beans, corn, tomato; heat through. Place 1/3 cup of mixture in tortillas, then 3 teaspoons cheese, and roll.
Place seam down in baking dish.
Continue with remainder. To enchiladas with onions, salsa and any remaining (or additional) cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve with sour cream, if desired.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant; slice and cook in salted water until tender. Drain, mash and season with salt and pepper to taste.
Add remaining ingredients to mixture and place in casserole.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: crme de menthe cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except chocolate syrup for 2 minutes. Put 2/3 of mixture into greased Bundt pan.
Add the chocolate syrup to remaining 1/3 batter and mix.
Pour this on top of first mixture.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes.
Run knife along inside and outside.
Invert onto plate.
When cool, drizzle with Chocolate Frosting.

title: apple pie
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Place rice in a 3-quart greased casserole.
Salt and pepper chicken; place on rice.
Mix other ingredients and pour over the chicken and raw rice.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° about 1 1/2 hours.

title: mediterranean bouillabaisse
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil.
Add tomatoes, clam juice, wine, parsley, salt, thyme, bay leaf and pepper and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Add shrimp, fish, scallops and crab legs. Cook 5 minutes.
Add clams and cook for another 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with salad and garlic bread.

title: jalapeno potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets in water until tender, but not falling
apart.
When
cool
enough to handle, peel, slice and layer
in
a
buttered
casserole
dish
with
bell pepper and pimento.
Salt
and
pepper each layer.
Grate or cube cheese. Melt
butter
in saucepan.	Add flour and stir.
Gradually add milk,
stirring constantly.
Add cheese and cook until melted. Pour over
potatoes
and
bake
at	350° about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
(If	you like a lot of cheese, use a whole roll of each cheese.)

title: four layer chocolate dessert
directions: First Layer:
Mix melted oleo, flour and sugar.
Add pecans; mix well.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes or until lightly brown and cool.

title: cashew brittle
directions: In a microwave-safe bowl, combine the sugar and corn syrup. Microwave, uncovered, on high for 4 minutes; stir.
Heat 3 minutes longer.
Stir in cashews and butter.
Microwave on high for 30-60 seconds or until mixture turns a light amber (mixture will be very hot).
Quickly stir in baking soda and vanilla until light and foamy.
Immediately pour onto a greased baking sheet and spread with a metal spatula.
Chill for 20 minutes or until set; break into small pieces.
Store in an airtight container.

title: creamy baked cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine. Press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie crusts.
Makes two (2) pies. Top with
Cool Whip or your favorite meringue.

title: cathy's swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, 1/2 can fried onions, sour cream and pepper.
Pour into 1-quart casserole. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken breasts, then roll in flour.
Bake chicken in butter until done, then pour off butter.
Boil orange juice, lemon juice, sugar, soy sauce and flour or cornstarch together.
Add pineapple chunks.
Pour over chicken.
Serve over rice.

title: crustless bacon and egg quiche
directions: Cook bacon until crisp and crumble.
Set aside.
In blender, combine milk, Bisquick, eggs, butter and pepper.
Blend for 15 seconds.
Pour into 9-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle with bacon and cheese, gently press in.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between edge and middle comes out clean. Let stand 10 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: coconut balls
directions: Heat until runny; add coconut.
Set in refrigerator for 1 hour or overnight.
Roll into balls.
Put in freezer.
Dip in chocolate, either bittersweet (like chocolate chips) or milk chocolate, whichever you prefer.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Brown minced onion in fat.
Brown flour in skillet.
Add tomatoes, cut okra, celery, chopped red pepper, chopped green pepper, cooked chicken and broth or water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Add cooked rice.

title: cocoa sigh
directions: In a small bowl, mix flour, cocoa, baking powder and baking soda.
In a large bowl, beat 3/4 cup sugar, milk and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in flour mixture; beat until evenly moistened. In another large bowl and using clean, dry beaters, whip egg whites on high speed until frothy.
Gradually beat in remaining 1/2 cup sugar (1 tablespoon at a time) until stiff, moist peaks form.
Immediately add to cocoa mixture, gently folding in with a wire whisk until evenly blended.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Tear lettuce into small pieces and place in 9 x 12-inch glass dish.
Layer next 5 ingredients in order given.
Add sugar to mayonnaise and spread over top as you would frosting.
Top with grated cheese and bacon.
Refrigerate 8 to 12 hours.

title: oven barbecue chicken
directions: Fry chicken in oil until browned.
Drain.
Place chicken in a long pan or baking dish.
In saucepan, saute onion in butter until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer uncovered for 15 minutes.
Pour over chicken and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until chicken is done, basting occasionally.

title: dutch three-layer cookies
directions: Mix and put in a 9-inch square pan.
Bake until brown.

title: barbecued chicken wings
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Add brown sugar to thicken.
Add or reduce ingredient amounts to taste.
Bake chicken wings at 450° for 30 minutes.
Coat with sauce and cook until done.

title: eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding, milk and Cool Whip by hand.
Cover bottom of 9 x 12-inch baking dish with whole graham crackers.
Put 1/2 of pudding mixture over crackers.
Top with whole graham crackers, then rest of pudding mixture, then crackers.
Top with frosting. Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: cheesy bell peppers
directions: Cut off tops of peppers and clean out.
Precook peppers by boiling in salted water for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle the inside with salt.
Saute in a skillet the beef and onions.
Drain off fat and add other ingredients.
Cover and simmer until tender, about 15 minutes.
Grate cheese.
Add to meat mixture.
Stuff peppers and top with catsup.
Set upright in oblong Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: e z spicy low-fat chili
directions: Brown turkey.
Add remaining ingredients into large pan; cook on low heat for at least 1 hour.

title: apple crisp
directions: Pare apples; slice thin.
Arrange slices in greased 8-inch round pan.
Combine oatmeal, sugar, flour and spices.
Cut in butter.
Sprinkle mixture over apples.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm with cheese wedge or whipped cream.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix flour, salt and soda and set aside.
Mix white sugar and cinnamon and set aside.
In a large bowl cream margarine and brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Using electric beater at low speed, beat in egg, then dry ingredients, alternating with milk until blended.
Stir in rhubarb and vanilla.
Turn into 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased and floured pan.*
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until it tests dry when toothpick is inserted.

title: frozen waldorf salad
directions: Cook the eggs, sugar, pineapple juice and salt over low heat, stirring until thick.
Cool.
May be refrigerated in closed container.

title: hermits
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and molasses.
Add dry ingredients and raisins. Form 1-inch diameter rolls.
Flatten to 1/4-inch.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes on ungreased sheet.
Slice into bars while still warm.

title: spinach gourmet
directions: Prepare and cook fresh spinach or Swiss chard as directed; chop and drain thoroughly.
Stir together spinach, mushrooms and seasonings in saucepan.
Blend sour cream and light cream; pour over spinach mixture.
Heat just to boiling.
Makes 4 servings.

title: taco soup
directions: Add all except celery and salsa.
Cook 30 minutes.
Add celery and cook extra 30 minutes.
Add cheese on top as garnish and chips (optional).

title: sweet egg custard
directions: Beat eggs, then add vanilla, lemon and sugar; beat together real well.
Add milk and pour mix in crust.
Bake at about 300° until done.
Serve with ice cream on top of pie.

title: tasty meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Mix well.
Place mixture into an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: strawberry dressing for fruit salad
directions: Combine strawberries and mayonnaise, then fold in yogurt. Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Serve over fresh fruit.
Makes 3 cups.

title: baked bean medley
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, combine the pork and beans, kidney beans, garbanzo beans and lima beans.
Mix well.
Stir in the onion, molasses, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, prepared mustard and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Bake, covered, in a 375° oven for 45 minutes or until onion is tender.
Garnish with onion rings and celery leaves, if desired.
Makes 10 servings.

title: beer bread
directions: Into large mixing bowl, pour beer, let "fizz."
Stir in the sugar, add self-rising flour and blend.
Mixed dough will be lumpy. Do not mix until smooth.
Spoon into 1 large (9 x 5 x 3-inch) or 2 small greased bread pans.
Pour the melted margarine over the dough.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Cool on rack.
This is just like the "Beer Bread" you can buy in stores.

title: jalapeno potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets until done; let cool.
Peel and slice. Place in baking dish; sprinkle with salt and pepper and add chopped bell pepper.
In double boiler, melt cheese, butter, milk and flour over medium heat, stirring until cheese has melted.
Pour cheese mixture over sliced potatoes making sure to cover all potatoes. Bake combined mixture in preheated oven at 350° until cheese mixture bubbles.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese softened sugar, vanilla, and lemon juice.
Mix with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs, mix until blended.
Pour into ready to use crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
(To check if the cake is ready, stick a fork in it.
If the fork comes out dry, its ready.)

title: cherry pineapple delight
directions: Layer ingredients in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Layer cherry pie filling, then crushed pineapple (with juice).
Sprinkle yellow cake mix on top.
Add melted butter.
Add coconut and pecans. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until a golden color.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in baking dish with meatiest portions toward outside of dish.
Pour barbecue sauce over chicken.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: caramel topped rolls
directions: Thaw slightly 1 loaf of bread; break into small pieces.
Place in one layer in greased pan, 9 x 13-inches.
Melt margarine; add dry pudding mix, brown sugar, cinnamon, milk and nuts.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cool slightly and pour mixture evenly over rolls.
Break other loaf of bread into small pieces and place on top of first layer.
Let rise to top of pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Flip out of pan immediately.

title: sunday supper chicken stew
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter (margarine) in large, heavy pot over medium heat.
Add celery and carrots.
Saute for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add mushrooms; saute for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove vegetables to a large bowl.
Set aside.

title: fudge cake
directions: Bring margarine, cocoa and water to a boil (can be done in microwave).
Add sugar, flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix well by hand.
Add eggs and sour cream or buttermilk.
Very lightly greased a 10 x 15-inch pan. Pour in mixture and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Careful not to overbake.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Combine shortening and scalded milk.
Combine eggs, sugar and salt; beat in cold water.
Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Mix all together and add flour.
Mix well and cover; leave in refrigerator until needed.
When ready to use, roll out dough and cut into rolls.
Let rise at least one hour.
Bake at 425°.

title: white tassle hamburgers
directions: Combine dry, minced onion and hot water in a cup and let stand about 10 minutes to soften.
In a medium mixing bowl combine the ground round with the strained beef and add clear beef broth. Shape the beef mixture into patties using 1/4 cup of meat mixture for each one.
Cut each hot dog bun into 2 equal pieces and cut off rounded ends.
On a lightly oiled griddle or electric skillet, fry patties over medium to high heat.
Make 3 or 4 holes in each patty with the spatula handle.
Place 1 tablespoon of onion next to the patty, then when you turn the patty, put it down on the onion.
Press firmly with the spatula to flatten and fry until well done.
Put the patty onto a bun half and serve with pickle chips, mustard and ketchup.
Serve promptly.

title: honey bran cookies
directions: Combine flour and baking powder. Cream butter and add honey gradually. Add egg and vanilla and beat well. Stir in bran and add dry ingredients. Add seeds. Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: peppers and sausage
directions: Brown sausage in oven at 350° until fat drains off (about 10 minutes on each side).
In frying pan, put oil, peppers and onion and fry until soft. Drain off oil. In 2 or 3-quart saucepan, add all ingredients. Simmer until done, about 3 to 4 hours.

title: **yum-yum salad
directions: Combine pineapple, lemon juice and sugar.
Heat until sugar is dissolved.
Mix gelatine in 1 1/2 cups cold water, let stand 10 minutes.
Add to pineapple mixture and let jell in refrigerator until thick.
Add cheese, pimento and Dream Whip and mix well. Let jell completely or overnight.

title: country corn fritters
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix corn and egg. Add to dry ingredients, stirring lightly.
Heat corn oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Drop batter by tablespoons into hot corn oil, one layer at a time. Fry about 2 minutes on each side or until golden brown. Drain on absorbent paper.
Makes 16 fritters.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind all together in food chopper.
Add as much sugar as fruit.

title: easy low-fat lasagna
directions: In a 10 x 13 x 2-inch microwave-safe dish, begin layering with sauce in bottom of pan.
Next, layer uncooked noodles, then spinach, then cheese(s), then noodles, sauce, spinach and so on. Try for 4 layers noodles minimum, ending with sauce on top of the last noodle layer.
Cover with heavy plastic wrap/wax paper and vent 1 corner.
Cook in microwave on High for 17 minutes.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Rotate 1/2 turn; cook at Medium for another 17 minutes.
Remove; let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Can sprinkle shredded Mozzarella or Parmesan on top before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: biscuits
directions: Melt butter and brush biscuits.
Bake at 350 degrees until golden brown.

title: cheese spread
directions: Soften cream cheese with beater.
Add other ingredients.
Let set in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: hot beer bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour batter into buttered loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Brush top with melted butter, if desired.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix together.
Put in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool slightly.

title: tomatoes vinaigrette
directions: Combine dressing ingredients and mix well.
Pour over sliced tomatoes and allow to marinate at least 2 hours at room temperature.
Delicious!

title: tender juicy pot roast
directions: Heat the oil in pan.
Season meat; add meat to pan.
Add 1/2 cup of water; let boil for about 1 hour.
When water is low, turn burner down to medium heat.
Let meat fry slowly, turning as needed.
When meat is tender, add onion.
Let cook for 10 minutes, then mix flour and water, stirring well.
Add to pot, then add potatoes.
Let cook until potatoes are done.

title: ratatouille 2
directions: Heat oil in heavy skillet; saute onions until they begin to color.
Add peppers; saute a few more minutes.
Add zucchini and eggplant (adding a little more oil if necessary).
Cook about 5 minutes.
Turn vegetables into large casserole.
Add tomatoes; cover.
Cook in preheated 250° oven for 1 1/4 hours.
Add parsley, garlic and seasoning; cook 20 minutes.
Sprinkle generously with cheese before serving.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: italian stuffed green peppers
directions: Remove seeds from peppers.
Parboil 5 minutes; drain.
Saute onion and garlic in margarine; stir in tomato sauce, rice, 1 cup cheese and oregano.
Spoon into peppers; place in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese; continue baking until cheese is melted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: "b j's doodles"
directions: Beat first four ingredients with mixer until creamy.
Add flour and cream of tartar.
Mix well.
By teaspoon roll into balls and roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cookie is best if not browned too much on the bottom.

title: crumb-topped beans
directions: Cook green beans according to package directions.
Meanwhile, in small saucepan, heat butter or margarine until lightly browned. Stir in the crumbs and parsley.
Drain beans and sprinkle with the crumb mixture.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate ice cream pie
directions: In a bowl whisk melted ice cream and pudding mix for 2 minutes. Pour into crusts. Freeze until firm. Pies may be frozen for up to 2 months. Remove from freezer 10 minutes before serving. Garnish with whipped topping if desired.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, milk and oleo to boil.
Boil hard 1 minute; remove from heat.
Add vanilla, oatmeal and peanut butter. Stir until mixed well.
Drop by spoon onto waxed paper.

title: goodies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, salt, milk and margarine in a pot.
Boil for 1 minute.
Take off heat.
Mix in peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Stir well.
With teaspoon, drop mixture onto wax paper.

title: cornmeal yeast muffins
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large bowl; let stand 5 minutes.
Combine milk and next 4 ingredients in a saucepan.
Cook over low heat until margarine melts.
Cool to 105° to 115°.
Add milk mixture to yeast mixture. Stir in egg substitute, cornmeal and 2 cups flour.
Beat at medium speed with an electric mixer until smooth. Stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.

title: glorified gingerbread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well and remove 1 cup.
Combine milk and vinegar.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with crumbs from removed 1 cup.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Test with a toothpick.

title: low-fat veggie dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.
Serve with broccoli, cauliflower, peppers, etc.

title: country style steak in crock-pot
directions: Put mushroom soup and water in crock-pot.
When steak is brown, put it in crock-pot.
Cook on low heat for several hours.

title: monkey bread
directions: Place nuts in bottom of Bundt pan before biscuits.
Cut biscuits into 4 pieces.
Mix cinnamon and sugar together.
Put pieces of biscuit in mixture.
Shake well.
Lay in greased pan; place one on top of the other.
Pour melted butter over biscuits and the rest of the mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from pan; pull apart to serve.

title: sausage-rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
Cook celery, onion and green pepper in 2 tablespoons sausage fat.
Combine soup with boiling water. Combine all ingredients in 2-quart casserole.
Cover.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Uncover.
Bake 15 more minutes.
Makes 6 large servings.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt together; blend in shortening and add milk.
Drop by tablespoonful onto boiling apple mixture.
Cover and cook for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften	cream cheese.
Grate other cheeses and mix well with cream
cheese.
Add other ingredients.
Form into ball or log. Roll
in crushed nuts.
Chill.
Remove from refrigerator about
30 minutes before serving.
Serve with favorite crackers.

title: fried pies
directions: Sift salt and baking powder with sifted and measured flour. blend in shortening.
Combine egg yolk, sugar and milk.
Stir into flour mixture.
Roll out on a floured board to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into circles 4 or 5-inches in diameter.
Spread
a small amount of cooked and sweetened dried fruit on half of each round.
Fold the other half of crust over filling.
Seal edges with a fork, dipped in flour.
Fry in deep fat at 360° or in skillet until brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.

title: tamale pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 400° to 450° until golden brown.

title: cubed steak casserole
directions: Salt and pepper the steak.
Roll in flour and brown in hot skillet.
In a buttered baking pan, layer steak, onion and potatoes.
Mix soup with water and milk.
Pour over layered ingredients.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil, then bake another 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Add sugar and peanut butter; mix well. Gradually add the milk. Fold in whipped topping. Spoon into the crust. Sprinkle with peanuts. Chill overnight. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: simple yeast rolls
directions: Add yeast to water, let stand a few minutes.
Stir to dissolve.
Combine milk, butter and sugar.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add eggs, salt and 2 cups flour; beat thoroughly.
Stir in yeast. Blend in remaining flour.
Beat 5 minutes.
Do not knead.
Brush with butter.
Cover with cloth and let rise until double in size, about 1 hour.
Form bits of dough into balls 1-inch in size. Place in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Brush with butter.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 2 dozen.

title: pecan kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add brown sugar and vanilla. Mix until stiff.
Pour egg white mix with pecans.
Place individually on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until they are medium brown in a 250° to 275° oven.

title: easy caramel corn
directions: Bring to boil 5 minutes; stir once in a while so it won't burn. After boiling 5 minutes, remove from heat and add 1/2 teaspoon soda (this will foam up).
Stir well.
Pour over corn and place on large cookie sheet with sides.
Bake 1 hour at 200°.
Great!

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients,
except bread crumbs and place in 3 to 4 quart
casserole
dish.
Cover with crumbs.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, salt and soda and add to Raisin Bran cereal in large mixing bowl.
Mix together eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Add to dry ingredients and mix well by hand, just until all ingredients are moistened.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Unused batter may be stored in refrigerator for several weeks.
Makes 72.

title: summer salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Add pineapple, juice and all.
Set in refrigerator until Jell-O begins to jell.
Mix remaining ingredients, except nuts, together; add to Jell-O.
Mix well.
Top with remaining cheese and nuts.
Chill 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Bring onions and potatoes to boil.
Cook until tender.
Drain half of liquid from potatoes.
Then pour into casserole dish and add all other ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: four step chocolate cheese cake
directions: Blend well and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: mock veal cutlets
directions: Spray frypan with buttery spray.
Take turkey breast slices and shake in crumbs.
Fry for a short time until cooked.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with mashed potatoes, vegetable and cranberry sauce.

title: lazy way macaroons
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add cream of tartar; beat until stiff peaks form.
Add sugar.
Add chips or sprinkles of choice.
Drop onto ungreased sheet covered with foil or brown paper.
Turn oven off; leave in oven for 4 to 5 hours or overnight.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in casserole.
Take biscuits and separate into as thin a layer as possible.
Then put on top of casserole and bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until biscuits in center are done.

title: easy fruit dip
directions: Mix and refrigerate.
Serve with fresh fruit tray.

title: colcannon
directions: Cook
potatoes;
drain.
Meanwhile
combine cabbage and onion and
cook
in a small amount boiling salted water for 15 minutes; drain.
Mash potatoes using electric mixer.
Beat in butter and as much milk as necessary to make fluffy.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in cabbage and onion.
Top with parsley.

title: apple dumpling deluxe
directions: For Dough:
In medium mixing bowl, combine egg and sour cream. In small bowl, stir together flour, 2 tablespoons sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add to sour cream mixture.
Mix well.

title: blueberry coffeecake
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes in 10 x 6-inch baking dish.

title: basic cookie recipe
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend all ingredients in a large bowl. Drop by teaspoons 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 10 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Combine zucchini and onion in medium saucepan; add water to cover and bring to a boil.
Boil for 5 minutes; drain and cool. Combine carrots, soup, sour cream and garlic powder in large bowl. Add zucchini/onion and chicken; mix.
Spread in buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
To prepare topping, melt butter in skillet; add bread stuffing and seasoning packet and toss well.
Sprinkle stuffing over casserole.
Top with cheese, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a bowl, mix all ingredients lightly and quickly.
Be careful not to overprocess the batter.
Turn the dough out onto a floured board and mold it into a large, round loaf. Place the loaf in a greased 9-inch round pan and make an "X" in the top with a knife.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until golden. Cool on rack.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Combine potatoes, salmon, eggs, lemon juice, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Add enough bread crumbs to handle mixture easily.
Shape into 8 patties.
Dip in egg white, then in remaining bread crumbs.
In a large skillet, heat oil.
Fry croquettes until golden brown on both sides.
Drain on a paper towel.
Serve with sauce.

title: dad's favorite chuck in foil
directions: Lay chuck steak on foil and pour soup mix over.
Wrap tightly in foil.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: fiery cajun shrimp
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients; pour half of mixture in a large ceramic heatproof dish.
Layer shrimp and lemon slices in sauce; pour remaining sauce over shrimp and lemon.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes or until shrimp are pink, stirring twice. Drain sauce and serve as dip for French bread.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: sugar-free cherry cream pie(diabetic)
directions: Mix the pudding mix as directed on package.
Spoon in a baked pie shell.	Drain one can of cherries.
Add 4 tablespoons flour or 2 1/2 tablespoons cornstarch to cherry juice.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add a few drops of red food coloring. Remove from heat and add 14 packets of Equal.
Spoon cherry mixture on top of pie.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: salmon patties
directions: Combine salmon, egg, onion, flour, cornmeal, salt and pepper to taste.
Press into medium patties.
Fry until brown on both sides.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Heat butter and oil together in a large skillet.
Add shrimp and saute 3 minutes or until pink.
With a slotted spoon, remove shrimp; set aside.
Add garlic and saute 1 minute.
Stir in parsley, lemon juice, salt, pepper and shrimp; cook 1 minute.
If desired, serve over rice.

title: cranberry or jelly sauce
directions: Wash cranberries; add to boiling water and boil slowly for 20 minutes.
Put through sieve, add sugar and cook 5 minutes longer. Turn into mold or glasses.
Cover with wax if in glasses.
If in mold, cover with wax paper or Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate.
It will keep for a long time.

title: holiday fruit drops
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar; add eggs, mixing well.
Stir in buttermilk.
Blend all dry ingredients; stir into creamed mixture. Stir in pecans, cherries and dates.
Chill at least one hour. Heat oven to 400°.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of dough about 2 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until almost no imprint remains when touched lightly. Makes about 8 dozen cookies.

title: can can brown bread
directions: Combine dates, raisins and baking soda in 1 cup water and boil. Cream the oleo and sugar. Add vanilla and egg; beat well. Add flour and mix until moistened. Pour in fruit mixture and add nuts.
Place a small amount of oleo in cans and put in oven until melted. Fill cans 2/3 full. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Slightly beat eggs and add rest of ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle cinnamon or nutmeg on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: creamy cranberry salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a bowl; mix well. Fold in whipped topping. Pour into a large casserole dish. Chill until serving time.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

Melt butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Mix graham cracker crumbs with butter and press evenly over bottom of pan. Sprinkle over, in layers, the chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, coconut and nuts. Pour sweetened condensed milk over the top. Bake for about 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned. Cut into bars when cooled completely. Makes 3 dozen bars. Enjoy!

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Rub potatoes with shortening.
Bake 1 hour to 1 1/4 hours.
Increase oven to 400°.
Cut potatoes across top and scoop insides out.
Mash potatoes.
Add milk in small amounts at a time.
Add soft butter, salt and pepper.
Beat until fluffy. Fill potato shells.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: crab salad
directions: Cool noodles until done.
Drain.
Add chopped crabmeat, chopped celery, chopped bell pepper and chopped boiled eggs.
Stir in mayonnaise to desired consistency.

title: brownies
directions: Melt margarine in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add the rest of the ingredients. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Put knife in middle.
If it comes out clean, it is done.

title: blender popovers
directions: Place all ingredients into blender container; cover.
Blend on high speed for 15 seconds.
Pour into hot greased popover pans. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake for 15 minutes longer.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly; add eggs, pumpkin and water.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and spices; add to pumpkin mixture.
Stir in nuts and raisins; pour into 2-quart greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate eclair pie
directions: Mix pudding, milk and Cool Whip together until thick.
Put layer of graham crackers on melted butter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put layer of pudding mix, layer of graham crackers.
Repeat until all pudding mix is used.
Final layer should be graham crackers.

title: potato and cabbage soup
directions: Cook cabbage for 15 minutes, then add potatoes.
Cook until soft.
Add salt and pepper.
Add milk and butter.
Heat, but do not boil.
Serve with crackers.

title: cinnamon bread
directions: Put 2 cups sugar and oil in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat at medium speed.
Add sifted flour and baking powder, a little at a time.
Add can of milk.
Mix together 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Place 1/2 cup chopped nuts on each pan bottom.
Add some batter, then cinnamon mixture.
Add more batter, then cinnamon for top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or depending on heat of oven, 60 to 65 minutes until it's dry on top.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Drain beans and corn; combine with onion, salt, cheese, sour cream and soup.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cracker crumbs, butter and almonds.
Spread over top of vegetable mixture. Bake at 350° about 35 minutes.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except crackers.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Crumble the crackers and spread over the vegetables.
Melt some margarine and pour over the crackers. Cover and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese tarts
directions: Mix until creamy the cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and eggs. Place small vanilla wafer in bottom of foil midget cup.
Fill cups 2/3 full with cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes.
Cool and top with canned cherry filling.

title: cocoa cake
directions: Cream the sugar, eggs and Crisco.
Add milk.
Fill a 1-cup container, putting the cocoa in first, then fill to the top with boiling water.
Add soda to the water and cocoa; stir.
It wil foam and run over into the sugar/egg mixture.
Dump entire contents of cup in and stir.
Mix in the dry ingredients:
flour, soda and salt; stir.
Add vanilla.
Bake in a greased and floured pan at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together and set aside.
Mix 2 tablespoons butter, brown sugar, walnuts and 1 teaspoon vanilla and set aside.
Cream remaining stick of butter and white sugar until light and fluffy.
Mix eggs, sour cream, bananas and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Blend in flour until just mixed. Reserve 1/4 cup nut mixture to sprinkle on top.
Pack rest into bottom of well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Pour batter on top and top batter with remaining nut mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until done.
Cool 10 minutes before turning out of pan.
Cool completely before cutting.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: spareribs with zesty honey sauce
directions: Combine chili sauce, honey, onion, Worcestershire sauce and mustard in small saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Sprinkle spareribs with salt and pepper. Place on rack in roasting pan; cover with foil.
Roast at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Uncover and brush generously with sauce.
Roast 45 minutes more and brush with sauce every 15 minutes until spareribs are fully cooked and tender.
Cut spareribs into serving portions and serve with remaining sauce.

title: stuffed mushrooms parmesan
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms; place caps open side up in a 13 x 9-inch oiled pan.
Set aside.
Chop mushroom stems and brown in butter with onion and garlic.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Pile lightly into caps.
Bake until tops brown and caps are tender at 400° (about 20 minutes).

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
(Put in oblong pan 9 x 13 x 2-inch.)
Note:
Instead of vanilla, can use teaspoon apple pie spice to flavor.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Cook and simmer the hamburger meat in the Ro-Tel; drain fat off.
Combine the first 6 ingredients.
Pour half of this mixture in the skillet (get it hot on top of stove).
Pour in the hamburger meat and put some cheese on top of that.
Pour the rest of the mixture in.
Cook in the oven until done at 425°.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Combine buttermilk and soda in a small bowl.
Let stand for a few minutes.
Beat egg whites until stiff in small bowl.
Set aside.
Cream the butter, shortening and sugar in a large bowl until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and buttermilk alternately, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Fold in egg whites.
Stir in pecans and coconut gently.
Pour into three 9-inch layer pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until cake tests done.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients except ham and pickles.
Spread mixture on sliced ham; add pickles end to end and roll.
Let set in refrigerator until cheese gets firmer, about 2 hours or more, then slice about 1/4-inch thick and serve on Ritz crackers.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Mix shortening, margarine and sugar, then add eggs and vanilla.
Add milk, then dry ingredients.
Roll out and cut out shapes.
If sticky, add flour to table to roll out.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.

title: no-bake cherry cheese cake #1
directions: Cream together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla. Dissolve jello in boiling water (let cool). Whip Carnation milk and fold into mixture.

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: Mix all together well.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
When done, cover with miniature marshmallows and let melt.
Leave in pan.

title: punch ice cream
directions: Mix sugar and junket; add milk and peaches.
Freeze in churn.

title: meatless lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles until almost done.
Using an oblong pan, layer with sauce and end with Parmesan cheese on top.
Sprinkle dried parsley on top, if desired.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Beat
cream
cheese
at medium speed of electric mixer. Stir in
cheeses
and
remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate in covered container.
Serve with crackers or use as a spread for sandwiches.

title: indian wheat-plantain
directions: Cook 2 to 3 minutes with cover on.
Plantain leaves can be dipped in milk or canned milk, then in flour and fried over low heat for 30 minutes.
Serve hot or cold like chips.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Cut stew meat into 1/2 inch chunks.
Shake in flour and brown in hot oil.
Add water, salt, pepper, bay leaf and garlic.
Cover; simmer 3 hours or until meat is very tender.
Add vegetables; cover and cook another 30 minutes.
Add spaghetti; cook 10 minutes.
Add seasonings to taste.
Yields 10-12 servings.

title: light fruit cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy; add well beaten eggs using rotary beater.
Blend well.
Chop nuts and fruit into medium sized pieces and flour with 1/2 cup flour.
Sift remaining flour and baking powder together.
Fold into egg and margarine mixture. Add flavorings.
Mix and then add fruit and nuts.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Place in cold oven and then bake at 250° for 3 hours.
Cool in pan.

title: spiced peach punch(hot drink)
directions: Combine peach nectar, orange juice and brown sugar in a large saucepan.
Tie cinnamon sticks and cloves in a cheesecloth bag and drop into saucepan. Heat slowly, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Simmer 10 minutes. Stir in lime juice.
Ladle into mugs. Serve warm.
Serves 12.

title: meatballs and gravy
directions: Brown meatballs in oil on all sides and then put into a casserole dish. Drain fat from frying pan, then add soup and 1/4 cup water to drippings; mix well.
Pour over meatballs and bake, covered in 350° oven 1 hour.
Serve with mashed potatoes or rice.

title: chourico salad
directions: Grind or chop chourico.
Remove strings from celery.
Remove seeds from sweet peppers.
Peel onions and chop all veggies. Place in pan and add ketchup, enough to cook for 1 hour.
Good warm or cold; can also be frozen for future use.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots in small amount of salted water until just tender, about 8 minutes; drain.
Combine with onions and green pepper in large bowl; stir together.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over vegetables and refrigerate several hours.
Makes about 5 cups. Will keep a couple of weeks in the refrigerator.

title: dinner rolls and cinnamon buns
directions: This recipe allows you to make fresh dinner rolls for the evening meal (with enough left over to freeze for another time) plus cinnamon rolls for breakfast the next morning!

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Brown hamburger. Mix in cream of mushroom soup, green beans and Mozzarella cheese. Cover bottom of casserole with mixture and flatten evenly. Cover with Tater Tots and Cheddar cheese. Bake for 45 minutes.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine flour and sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse corn meal. Press firmly in bottom of pan (13 x 9-inch).
Bake 15 minutes.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all together. Pour into 3 greased round pans. Bake for about 45 minutes or until done. Cool before you ice.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes in slightly salted water; drain well.
In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs and add mayonnaise, white sauce, onions, water chestnuts and cheese.
Mix well.
Add broccoli and pour into casserole dish. Cover with Ritz cracker crumbs and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mock lobster
directions: Cut up frozen fish.
Bring seasoned water to boiling; add fish. Simmer 20 minutes.
Drain and serve by dipping in melted butter.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and butter together.
Fold in nuts, raisins, coconut and lemon juice.
Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake for 40 minutes at 375°.

title: deb's salad dressing
directions: Mix with electric blender; store in refrigerator.

title: caramel icing
directions: Thoroughly mix 2 1/2 cups sugar and milk in heavy saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Turn down to medium heat.
Caramelize the 1/2 cup remaining sugar.
Add to icing.
Stir constantly.
Cook about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute onion and carrots in margarine or water until tender. Add mushroom soup and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Wash zucchini and cut in cubes.
Steam zucchini until tender.
Drain and add to the sauteed mixture.
Add the bread crumbs.
Put in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: fruit whip (salad)
directions: Beat cream cheese and condensed milk until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping and fold in well-drained fruit.
Top with a few cherries.

title: grandma's stuffed potato boats
directions: Remove foil from potatoes.
Slice the potatoes in half lengthwise.
Scoop the inside of the potatoes into a bowl.

title: gourmet beef fricassee
directions: Brown meat in hot fat.
Add remaining ingredients, except flour.
Cover and simmer 2 hours.
Blend flour with a small amount of cold water; add to meat.
Cook until thick.
Serve with rice, noodles or mashed potatoes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: kielbasa and beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a 2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered, Remove cover and bake approximately 45 minutes longer. Can be doubled for large crowd.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix in baking pan (do not sift flour).
Bake at 350° until crust is brown.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: fruit pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice together; add fruit.
Add Cool Whip and pour into 2 graham cracker pie shells.
Ready to eat!

title: pumpkin crisp
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle dry mix over this and sprinkle nuts over this.
Pour melted oleo over all.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Can serve with Cool Whip, whipped cream or ice cream.

title: chicken bits in sauce
directions: Cut chicken into bite sized pieces.
Place flour in a plastic bag and season with the salt and pepper.
Add chicken pieces a few at a time to coat with seasoned flour.
Saute chicken in butter and olive oil until golden brown on both sides.
When all th chicken is cooked, add the can of chicken broth which will thicken to make a sauce.
Serve with white rice.

title: congealed peach salad
directions: Bring pineapple with juice, water, and sugar to a boil. Remove from heat and add Jello.
Chill until partially set.
In separate bowl, beat cream cheese and gradually add milk.
Combine Cool Whip with cheese mixture and fold into gelatin mixture. Chill until set.

title: mrs. thigpen's rocks
directions: Cream butter and sugar together, then add spices, salt and soda that was dissolved in hot water.
Then beat and add eggs; alternate, adding flour, fruits and nuts until all has been added. Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: double decker tacos
directions: Brown meat in large skillet on medium heat; drain.
Add taco seasoning.
Spread each soft tortilla with 2 tablespoons beans. Place crisp taco shell over beans.
Fold soft tortilla over taco shell.
Fill taco shells with seasoned meat.
Top with cheese, sour cream and your favorite taco fixings, such as chopped tomato, shredded lettuce and taco sauce.

title: hot melt cake
directions: Beat eggs until lemon-color, add sugar.
Beat until like marshmallow.
Add flour.
Melt butter in milk and add.
Add vanilla, salt and baking powder last.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
After baking, remove cake.
Take 1 stick butter or margarine and run over top of cake.
Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar or 10x sugar.

title: refrigerator yeast bread
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in shortening and sugar.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
In a large mixing bowl, stir together milk, yeast and 6 cups flour.
Let stand until bubbly.

title: asparagus puffs
directions: Bring to boil milk, water, butter, salt, cayenne and coriander. Reduce heat to low. Add flour all at once. With wooden spoon, beat until it pulls away from bottom and sides. Let cool 4 minutes. Transfer warm dough to food processor. Pulse 5 times. Add eggs, one at a time. Process until dough is smooth and shiny. Heat oven to 400°. Butter 2 baking sheets. Line with paper. Butter paper. Blanch asparagus and chop. Mix asparagus and cheeses into dough. Spoon rounded teaspoonfuls. Smooth with brush. Bake 1 sheet at a time for 25 minutes.

title: toasted almond party spread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and mix well. Spread mixture into 9-inch pie plate or quiche dish.
Bake for 15 minutes, stirring after 8 minutes. Garnish with additional toasted almonds, if desired. Serve with assorted crackers or toasted bread cut-outs.

title: fudge
directions: Heat sugar, butter, cocoa, milk, vanilla and salt in a saucepan, stirring until smooth.
Stir in pecans.
Spread mixture in buttered pan.
After mixture has cooled, cut into squares.

title: shrimp chowder
directions: Heat oil and saute onion until well cooked, but not browned. Add flour and mix well.
Add potatoes and water with chicken base. Cover tightly and boil until potatoes are tender, but not broken. Add shrimp, cream, salt and peppers.
Heat until warm (don't boil)!
Sprinkle with parsley and serve.

title: spiced tea
directions: When brewing the tea, place the cinnamon sticks in the same pan or teapot.
When the tea is ready, discard the cinnamon sticks.
Add the remaining ingredients and serve, or chill first and serve over ice cubes if you want iced tea.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown the ground meat in frying pan.
Bring 2 cups water to boil.
Add the potatoes, butter, salt and pepper; mix.
In baking dish, add browned meat and vegetable soup, then top with potatoes sealed to edges of dish.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix stuffing mix and hot water.
Break sausage in small pieces and add to stuffing mix.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Make into small patties.
Bake in covered pan for 10 minutes at 400°, then at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Layer in a casserole dish as follows:
ground beef, cream of mushroom soup, Durkee onions and cheese.
Top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter popcorn
directions: Keep popped corn warm in 225° oven.
In a saucepan, combine sugar and syrup.
Cook and stir until it comes to a full boil. Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour over popped corn.
Stir to coat all the popped corn.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix together the grape jello and the boiling water.
Add the blueberry pie filling and the crushed pineapple.
Congeal.

title: clam canapes
directions: Whip the cheese with a fork.
Add clams and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and whip well.
Place in refrigerator.
When ready to serve, heap generously on plain white salty crackers and bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, and mix. Add vanilla, mashed bananas and sour cream.
Mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Grease and flour a loaf pan; pour in mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until brown.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Melt margarine; add flour and nuts.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix cream cheese with powdered sugar and 1/2 large Cool Whip.
Spread over cool crust.
Mix 3 cups milk with 2 packages of instant pudding.
Spread on top of cream cheese layer.
Spread rest of Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle grated chocolate on top.
Refrigerate at least 1 1/2 hours before serving.

title: frozen fruit slushwestboro, missouri
directions: Partially thaw frozen fruits and concentrates, combine with other fruits, water and sugar.
May be frozen in individual cups or in one container.
tags: flavoring of one of the fruits

title: cran-raspberry liqueur
directions: Coarsely chop cranberries.
In a 2-quart glass jar with lid, combine all ingredients; stir until sugar is dissolved.
Cover tightly with lid.
Allow to stand at room temperature 2 weeks, inverting jar everyday.
Strain through cheesecloth.
Pour into decorative bottles; cap tightly.
Serve in chilled glasses. Serving size:
1/2 cup.
Servings:

title: praline strips
directions: Grease a cookie sheet and line with graham crackers.
Mix brown sugar and oleo; boil for 2 minutes.
Add pecans; pour this filling on top of crackers.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with graham cracker crumbs; carefully spread with back of spoon.
Top evenly with condensed milk.
Sprinkle with chocolate bits, chopped nuts and flaked coconut, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: german pancakes
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix remaining ingredients well in blender and pour over melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 18 minutes without opening oven door.
Serve with hot syrup.

title: barbara's blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jello, add blueberries and pineapple.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Cut crust off bread. Cut bread into strips as wide as your finger. Put into 200° oven for 1 1/2 hours. Put oil and peanut butter in double boiler; warm and mix well. Mix cracker crumbs and sugar together. Dip 1 strip at a time in peanut butter, then roll in crumb mixture. Place on wax paper to dry.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Mix and
pour
into greased 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Add boiling water to Bisquick and softened
butter.
Stir
vigorously with fork until dough forms ball
and
cleans the bowl.
Pat out between 2 pieces of wax paper,
dusted
with
flour/Bisquick
to
fit over top of berries in	baking dish.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Can be topped with whipped cream.

title: bollos (round bread)
directions: In large bowl, combine salt, 3 cups flour and yeast. Heat margarine and the milk (125-130°). hot to the touch. Add to dry mixture, then add water. Add egg.
Knead by hand, adding remaining flour, until dough is no longer sticky.

Dough must be smooth and like elastic. Cover and let rest for 10 min. Cut dough in half, press each down. Prick with fork 3 times. Cover and let rise for 1 hour. (On top of refrigerator). Place breads on oven racks. Bake at 350° for 20 min.

title: pepper chicken
directions: Chop chicken breast into bite size; cook in skillet until breast is white.
Chop green pepper into skillet; add mushrooms, then put 4 to 5 shakes of soy sauce into skillet and let cook together 10 to 15 minutes.
Cook rice until done; put on plate, then add mix on rice.

title: layered ham snacks
directions: Mix cream cheese,
sauce, Miracle Whip, onion and horseradish. Layer a piece of ham and spread cream mixture on it, repeat until everything is used. Chill in refrig. until set.
Cut into little squares and serve with toothpicks.

title: slim spanish rice(sugar-free)
directions: Drain and coarsely chop tomatoes, reserving juice.
Add water to juice to equal 1 1/3 cups.
Bring to a boil in small saucepan. Stir in all ingredients.
Cover tightly and simmer 20 minutes. Remove from heat; let stand, covered, until most of liquid is absorbed, about 5 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Makes 2 servings.

title: quick italian casserole
directions: Prepare pasta; drain.
Place in casserole dish.
Pour sauce over pasta.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover.
Microwave on Medium/high 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: teriyaki stew
directions: Brown meat in the oil in a skillet.
Place in a large pot. Cover with boiling water.
Add bay leaves, monosodium glutamate, salt, pepper, soy sauce, celery, carrot and onion.
Cook slowly for at least an hour until the meat is tender.
Take out the bay leaves, celery and carrot.
Add the cut celery and carrots and the small onions.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Add more water if needed. Add the next 4 ingredients; cook for 10 minutes.

title: italian sausage appetizers
directions: Cook Italian sausage in oven under broiler, being careful not to overcook.
Slice into bite size rounds, place into Pyrex dish and coat with barbecue sauce.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all, except mayonnaise, the night before; cover and refrigerate.
Before serving or next morning, stir in mayonnaise.

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: Saute garlic, zucchini, onion, green pepper until tender (4-5 minutes) add tomatoes, pepper, basil and parsley.
Simmer about 10 minutes, top with cheese and serve.

title: scallops in cream sauce
directions: Cook and stir onion in margarine in 10 inch skillet over medium high heat until tender.
Stir in scallops and salt.
Cook, stirring frequently, until scallops are white, 3 to 4 minutes.

title: honey mustard
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: cheesy italian popcorn(microwave dish)
directions: Melt butter over low heat and mix in the Parmesan cheese.
Use a big spoon to drizzle it over the popcorn.
Sprinkle just a bit of onion salt and pepper on, and then maybe a couple shakes of Parmesan cheese if you have any left.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla. Add all dry ingredients. Alternate with sour cream, mixing well after each addition. Chill several hours or overnight.
On lightly floured board, roll out dough to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut out.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Sprinkle with sugar and nutmeg.
Bake in a 450° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: red, white and blue jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Put in 7 x 11-inch dish.
Let set.

title: whacky cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add oil, vinegar and water.
Bake at 350° for 35 or 40 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Coat an 8 x 8-inch casserole dish with cooking spray.
Mix all ingredients.
Spread in dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Stir after 15 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake 1 hour in 325° oven in two lightly oiled loaf pans.

title: squash relish
directions: Soak first 4 ingredients in 3 quarts of water and 3/4 cup salt for 1 hour; drain well.
Mix last 4 ingredients in a large pot. Bring to a boil.
Add drained vegetables and bring to boil again. Do not cook.
Put in jars and seal.
Chill before serving.

title: mary ball washington (1784) gingerbread
directions: Cream the butter. Add brown sugar and beat well. Add molasses, honey, sherry and milk.
Beat very well. Sift flour and cream of tartar.
Add alternately with beaten eggs to sugar mixture.
Add orange rind and juice. Add raisins and baking soda that you dissolved in warm water.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Line with wax paper.
Grease paper.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: sweet potatoes from martin luther king's restaurant in new orleans
directions: Mix ingredients in cooking pot.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: party pizza
directions: Brown beef and sausage separately. Drain and the mix together. Add 1 cup grated Velveeta cheese to warm mixture of ground beef and sausage.
Serve on rye. Add taco seasoning, if desired.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, carrot, sweet pepper and salt.
Let stand 1 hour and then drain.
Boil sugar, vinegar, water and mustard or celery seed.
Boil 1 minute.
Let cool and pour over chopped vegetables.
Mix and pour into containers and put in freezer.
Take out of freezer and thaw to eat.

title: baked boneless chicken breasts
directions: Butter 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Spread chipped beef on bottom of dish.
Cut breasts in half and wrap 1/2 piece of bacon around it.
Place in dish on top of beef.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken and cover.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake for 3 hours at 300°.
Take cover off and bake 1/2 hour longer to brown.
Serves 8.

title: finger jello
directions: Let set until firm, cut in pieces and eat with fingers.

title: depression cake or war time cake(stella smith)
directions: In saucepan, mix sugar, 1 1/4 cups water, shortening, raisins, nutmeg, cinnamon and cloves.
Boil 3 minutes; cool.
Dissolve salt and soda in 2 teaspoons water.
Add to mixture; blend in flour mixed with baking powder.
Pour into greased, floured 8-inch square pan.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 50 minutes.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Put tomatoes, onions and salt in a container.
Cover with water and set overnight.
In the morning drain and rinse.
Put into jars.
Mix vinegar, sugar and pickling spice in a pan and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Pour over tomatoes.

title: shortcake
directions: In a large bowl, mix flour, salt and baking powder.
In another bowl, blend sugar, eggs, milk and oleo.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9-inch square pan. Bake at 375° until lightly brown (about 25 to 30 minutes).

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into a ball.
Reserve some of the nuts to roll cheese ball in.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: In small bowl, combine cream cheese, butter and vanilla. Beat at low speed until light. Gradually add sugar, beating until fluffy. If necessary, add milk to make of spreading consistency.

title: bell pepper cheese ball
directions: Mix cheeses and other ingredients.
Roll into small logs or big ball.
Roll in chopped pecans to coat each log or ball.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed on box.
Add all ingredients except paprika and cheese.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with paprika and Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet and sour green beans
directions: Fry bacon; save the grease.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
To the grease, add vinegar and sugar.
Drain green beans and add them to vinegar mixture.
Simmer for 45 minutes or until the juice is about all gone.
Add bacon and serve.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti as directions say on box.
Mix spaghetti with the eggs that are beaten and the Parmesan cheese.
Put mixture in a 9-inch greased pie pan.
Mold the mixture like you would with pie crust (on the sides and bottom).

title: potato salad and dressing
directions: Cover with salad dressing as follows; let set for 6 hours.

title: idaho potato cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: confetti bites(vegetable pizza)
directions: Place two 8 ounce packages of crescent rolls into a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking sheet to form a crust.
Bake in 350° oven 12 to 15 minutes.
Combine two 8 ounce packages cream cheese, mayonnaise, basil leaves and garlic powder.
Spread thinly over cooled crust. Top with chopped vegetables.
Sprinkle generously with Salad Supreme.

title: jo jo potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice in quarters.
Dip potatoes in egg, then in flour.
Deep fry them.
Use dressing mix as directed on package.

title: chicken and shrimp in brochette(serves 4)
directions: Combine wine, lemon juice, oil, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, thyme, rosemary and parsley.
Cover and refrigerate on shrimp and chicken 2 to 4 hours, turning.

title: stir-fry beef
directions: Slightly heat oil in wok or frying pan.
Add onions and stir a few moments.
Add the meat and let simmer for 5 minutes.
Add the carrots and green pepper and stir-fry a few moments.
Add the mushrooms, bean sprouts and soy sauce; stir-fry a few more moments and serve with rice.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes on cookie sheet covered with aluminum foil for even baking.
Insulated cookie sheet works even better.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Blend shortening and sugar.
Add molasses and egg; beat well. Mix flour and spices.
Roll in 1-inch balls and dip top side in sugar.
Do not pat down.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: two-hour crusty italian bread
directions: Place yeast, sugar, salt and oil in large mixing bowl.
Cover mixture with 3 cups flour.
Add 2 cups very warm water.
Beat 5 minutes until dough is elastic.
Add 2 cups flour.
Mix thoroughly.
Cover bowl with dish towel and let dough rest 10 minutes in warm place.
Knead dough 5 minutes on floured surface, adding more flour if dough is sticky.
Knead no more than 5 minutes.
Cut dough in half and shape into long oval loaves and place on greased cookie pan.
Cut diagonal slits in top of loaves with sharp knife.
Let rise in warm place (85°) or warm oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes until loaves sound hollow when tapped with fingers.
Remove and allow to cool on rack.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix and bake in a 9 x 13 pan at 375° to 400°.
The cake will rise and fall.
Cut into bars.
Keep covered to retain moisture and these will keep for days.

title: mom's squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in water until tender; drain and mash.
Save 1 1/2 cups of juice.
To juice, add rest of ingredients (except 1 cup dressing mix).
Mix together; add to squash.
Top with remaining dressing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 large casseroles.

title: rice krispie dessert
directions: Melt butter; add brown sugar and rest of ingredients, except ice cream.
Put half of the mixture in the bottom of a spring-form pan.
Add the softened ice cream, then put the rest of the mixture on top and freeze overnight.

title: crabmeat appetizers
directions: Combine all ingredients and spread on English muffins.
This amount will usually do for a package of English muffins.
This can be frozen for later use.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° until done.
Do not overbake.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place raw pork chops in long baking dish.
On top of each chop, put 1 tablespoon raw rice.
On the rice, place 1 tablespoon tomatoes, then on tomatoes place 1 slice of onion.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover with hot water up to top of pork chops. Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: the best peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Dip fork in sugar, crisscross and flatten cookies.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: 14-day cole slaw
directions: Chop cabbage, onion, celery and green pepper finely.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
In a small saucepan, bring sugar, turmeric, mustard seed and vinegar to boiling point.
Remove from heat. Pour over chopped ingredients.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour tube pan or Bundt pan. Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Fold in chocolates.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When done, sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Make a well in center.
Add eggs, buttermilk and shortening; stir just to moisten.
Cover and store in refrigerator until ready to bake (as long as 5 to 6 weeks).

title: carrot cake
